title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine
sugar, butter and milk.
Place on medium heat. When it	starts	boiling, boil for five minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Hand beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft; add crab meat, mayonnaise, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
(If doing ahead, refrigerate until ready to use.)
Cover bread rounds generously with crab meat mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Broil under low heat a few minutes until golden brown and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter. Cool slightly.
Mix with sour cream, Cheddar cheese, soups, ham, hash browns and seasonings.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
In frypan, melt 1/2 stick butter.
Mix with 1 1/2 cups croutons and stir until brown. Spread over potatoes.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: freida's hot chocolate icing
directions: In a saucepan combine butter, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot cake.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
soda,
sugar
and dry pudding mix together.
In
a
large
mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat butter, brown
sugar, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually
beat
in
flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop
by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Preheat
oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 minutes or until done.
Transfer to rack to cool.

title: homemade chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, vanilla, egg yolks, corn starch, and milk. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into 9 inch baked pie shell and let cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake 2 tubes of crescent rolls on cookie sheet and cool.
Mix cream cheese with Ranch dressing to taste and spread on crescent rolls.
Sprinkle assorted vegetables onto cream cheese, pressing down lightly.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: spinach casserole 1
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: picante sauce
directions: Grind garlic, peppers and onions in meat grinder.
Cook tomatoes and other vegetables together with sugar and salt until it thickens as you like your sauce, stirring constantly.
Put in hot jar and seal.
Put sealed jars in hot water bath for 5 minutes. Make sure they are sealed.

title: cinnamon pull-aparts
directions: Put sugar and cinnamon in paper bag.
Shake well.
Add cut up biscuits so that each piece is coated.
Put in well-greased Bundt pan, one over the other, using all the cut-up biscuits.
Pour Cinnamon and Oleo mixture over the biscuits and bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle in half of the biscuits and then half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until medium brown.
Turn out on a plate.
Spread icing and eat with fingers.

title: no fuss pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking
dish; salt and pepper to taste. Pour sauce over chops, then top with onion and mushrooms.
Cover with foil.
Cut 4 slits in foil.
Cook in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: calabaza dulce(sweet pumpkin)
directions: Pour water into a large container with a rack.
Bring water to a boil using high heat.
Remove seeds and membrane center from pumpkin and discard.
Cut pumpkin into wedges (do not peel).
Place pumpkin on rack over boiling water.
Cover container and steam pumpkin at medium heat for 30 minutes or until pulp is tender.
Dot pumpkin with margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with pastry blender or fork until flaky.
Reserve 1/2 cup for use on the top.
Into balance of mixture, add milk, and egg and soda mixed together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
To 1/2 cup reserved for top, add 4 or 5 chopped Heath bars and the chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over top of batter and bake in 350°
oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve as is or add whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: rice pizza
directions: Combine rice, eggs and 1 cup cheese.
Press firmly into greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 20 minutes.
Combine sauce.
Spread evenly over crust.
Add toppings.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush cookies; add fruit, nuts and coconut.
Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Then add to cookie mixture; mix well. Then pack into 2 loaf pans that have been lined with wax paper. Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 2 to 3 cakes.
Does well when frozen also.

title: ozark honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, honey, soda and salt thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonful into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar. Add syrup and milk. Cook over medium heat until mixture forms a soft ball (232° F). Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into a greased (buttered) pan to cool. After cooled, slice into small squares.

title: mandarin salad
directions: In large bowl mix drained pineapple and oranges.
Add coconut and pecans.
Refrigerate and chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip; mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
When ingredients are blended, mix together the flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Batter is thick.
Mix for 1 minute or until well blended.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes (about) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use toothpick test for doneness because of thicker batter.

title: monkey bread(yields 1 cake)
directions: Spray Bundt or tube pan with nonstick spray.
Cut individual biscuits into quarters and roll in cinnamon/sugar mix.
(An easy way to do this is to put cinnamon/sugar in a plastic carton, throw in cut-up biscuits, snap on lid and shake it.)
Layer in pan with pecans and raisins, adding handful or so of pecans and raisins and some of the cinnamon/sugar mix after each can of biscuits.
For sauce, bring sugar, milk and butter to boil in saucepan.
Pour over biscuits in tube pan.
Bake in oven preheated to 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Dump out of pan onto dish or platter big enough to catch sauce.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer as stated.
For an extra twist, add a layer of fresh chopped cilantro!
Nuke for 7 to 9 minutes, until cheese melts. Or bake at 450° until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put all ingredients in dish you wish to cook in.
Mix well. Cook on 450° until it begins to bubble, then mix biscuits.
Add to top.
Reduce heat to 350°.

title: 3-3-3 pork chop casserole(3 ingredients, 300~ oven, 3 hours)
directions: Place 1 can apple pie filling in oblong baking dish.
Top with pork chops, salt and pepper to taste.
Top with Stove Top dressing (mixed according to directions on package first).
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: valencia salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shake until sugar dissolves. A good dressing to use on tossed green salad; really compliments French dip sandwiches when served with salad.

title: uncooked cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and dry fresh picked cucumbers.
Pack in clean dried quart fruit jars until full. Add vinegar to cover cucumbers. Last, add the salt (do not use iodine salt) and alum.
Set away for 6 weeks.
After 6 weeks, drain off vinegar completely.
Place in jar 3 cinnamon sticks and fill jars with sugar.
When sugar dissolves, re-fill jars again with sugar.
Again set away for 7 days. After 7 days, it is now ready to eat.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and sugar together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix jello with water.
Add strawberries.
Chill until syrupy and pour over cheese mixture.
Chill until ready to use.
Lime jello and crushed pineapple may be substituted for strawberries.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into oblong cake pan.
Combine cream cheese, 3 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: liver casserole
directions: Slice onions in pan and fry until light brown.
Mix flour, salt, mustard and sugar.
Dip the liver in this mixture.
Put half of onions in casserole.
Place the liver on top, then add rest of onions.
Mix curry powder to the rest of flour mixture.
Add the water and catsup, making a paste.
Pour over liver and onions. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: orange diabetic muffins
directions: Soak raisins in warm water for an hour; drain.
Mix orange juice, peel and raisins.
Cream sugar replacement, egg and margarine; add vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Combine all ingredients.
It should be like a thick cake batter.
(I needed to add a little water.)
Fill well-greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix together and chill 3 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Blend Crisco into flour.
Add milk.
Stir in with a fork. When all the flour and Crisco mixture is moist, dump onto a dough cloth and sprinkle a little extra flour over this to make it manageable.
Knead lightly.
Roll out with rolling pin or pat out gently by hand.
Cut out biscuits and place on cookie sheet that is slightly greased.
Bake at 425° until done, but not too long.

title: cabbage roll hot dish
directions: Parboil cabbage.
Brown hamburger, bacon and onions (mix). Layer cabbage, rice, hamburger, bacon and onion mixture.
Layer until all are used up.
Pour tomato sauce over and put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: indiana yummy pudding
directions: First Layer:
Mix the flour, sugar, chopped nuts and margarine together.
Pour into a 9 x 15-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: garden salad with green goddess dressing(lo-fat)
directions: In a food processor, puree the cottage cheese 3 minutes or until very smooth. Transfer to a large bowl. Whisk in mayonnaise, lemon juice, Parmesan, shallots or scallions, parsley, mustard, tarragon, pepper and garlic. Cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix and leave in refrigerator overnight for flavor to blend.

title: chili puffed eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, melt 4 tablespoons of the butter. Add the peppers and onion and saute over moderate heat until softened, about 10 minutes. In a large bowl, beat the eggs, salt, pepper and cream until blended. Pour over the pepper-onion mixture. Reduce the heat to low and cook, stirring constantly, until eggs are softly set, about 15 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in the remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Spoon about 1/2 cup of the scrambled eggs into the center of each of the 8 tortillas. Roll into a loose cylinder and place in pairs, seam side down, in a lightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle both cheeses evenly over the tortillas. Bake until the cheese is melted and the tortillas and eggs are warmed through, about 10 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine until they are transparent.
Add broth and pepper to onions and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve in oven-proof bowls.
Top with croutons and cheese (Swiss, Provolone or Mozzarella).
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: jello pie
directions: Stir sugar, crushed pineapple and Jell-O together.
Heat in saucepan until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool for about 5 minutes.
Whip chilled evaporated milk until double in volume.
Combine boiled mixture and whipped milk.
Pour into pie crusts and chill at least 4 hours.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Place pecans and coconut in bottom of greased pan.
Prepare German chocolate cake according to directions on the package. Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese in saucepan just enough to dissolve.
Pour over cake mixture.
Spoon confectioners sugar over cake mix.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Place zucchini in colander.
Sprinkle with salt; set aside for 30 minutes.
Squeeze as much liquid as possible from zucchini. Combine all ingredients, except oil.
Lightly grease skillet or griddle with oil and heat.
Drop slightly rounded tablespoonfuls of the batter onto the skillet.
Flatten to 3-inch diameter with back of spoon.
Cook, turning once, 1 minute on each side, or until golden.
Serve with sour cream if you wish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Make Jell-O
using
the 1 cup boiling water; set aside. Peel and cut
up
oranges and bananas.
Put in large bowl. Add the pineapple
and
lemon
juice.
Stir
in sugar; add Jell-O. Stir, then
cover
and refrigerate.
After several hours, stir again, then
refrigerate overnight or several hours more until set.

title: easiest-ever cocoa fudge
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in micro-proof bowl.
Microwave at High for 2 to 3 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla; blend well.
Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: grilled chicken salad
directions: Grill chicken over medium coals for 15 to 18 minutes, turning once, or until tender.
Remove from grill and place in a single layer on a platter; sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside.
In a large bowl, toss pasta, red pepper, celery, onion and dill.
Remove chicken from platter; pour juices into a bowl.
Slice chicken crosswise into thin strips; add the pasta mixture.
To the juices, add vinegar, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper; whisk well.
Add oil very slowly in a stream until dressing is thickened.
Pour over salad and toss.
Serve in a lettuce-lined bowl or on individual lettuce-lined plates.

title: chicken caribbean
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.

title: hash brown potato dish
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup oleo.
Pour in baking dish.
Mix crumbs with other oleo.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans with ingredients except corn flakes.
Put in greased casserole.
Cover with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fruit loop confections
directions: Melt white chocolate bark with paraffin wax over hot water. Do not boil.
Pour over Fruit Loops, marshmallows and chopped nuts; toss until well coated.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Heap crock-pot full of apples.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt over top.
Cover and cook on high until heated through.
Set on low and cook all day.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Peel and chop carrots.
Add water and cook in microwave 30 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and Velveeta until melted.
Pour over carrots.
Melt 1 stick butter; set aside. Crush crackers and mix with butter.
Pat over carrots, like a crust.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: fruit medley
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Add garlic and/or onion to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top for color.

title: kraut and chops
directions: Wash pork chops in cold water.
Place in large casserole dish. Season the pork chops with seasoned salt.
Cook in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
After the chops have cooked, pour in bag of kraut. Let cook slowly for 20 minutes at 250°.

title: *stuffed cabbage with lemon sauce
directions: Place cabbage in pot filled with boiling water. Boil for 10 minutes. Separate leaves. Combine meat, rice, onion, salt, pepper and parsley.
Place about 2 tablespoons of filling in each cabbage leaf.
Loosely fold over sides and roll.
Place rolls into large pot, keeping them tight.
Dot with the butter and pour the 3 cups of hot water into pot.
Bring to a boil and cook over low heat for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix 1
cup
of water with the soup and heat.
Drain the asparagus,	place
in
a microwavable bowl and microwave, covered, about 2 minutes on High until hot.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, Pam sprayed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Spread wings in jelly roll pan in a single layer.
Drain the pineapple well and mix with other ingredients.
Spread mixture over wings.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, turning wings every 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: If desired, add diced bananas or coconut to pudding.
Layer: 1 cake layer, pineapple, pudding, 1 cake layer, pie filling and Cool Whip.
Top with nuts.

title: myrtle's brown sugar christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: camporee cassoulet(method:  one pot)
directions: Brown ground beef, celery, onion, green pepper, garlic and salt until onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in the remaining ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix and bake in Bundt pan or tube pan according to box directions.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pie filling and eggs together.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring the chicken broth to a boil over moderate heat.
Mix the cornstarch with the water and stir it into the broth.
Add the soy sauce, optional ginger, and pepper.
Return the soup to a boil and remove from heat.

Beat the eggs slightly, so that they are broken up but the yolks and the whites are not completely mixed together. Slowly pour the eggs into the soup while gently stirring to form long threads of the eggs.
Divide the scallion slices between the individual serving bowls and ladle the soup over them.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Add ingredients together; bring to a boil and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate for a couple of days.

title: easy chicken stew with scallion dumplings
directions: Combine chicken breasts and stock in a large pot; bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer for at least 10 minutes, but a half hour won't hurt.
Add the carrots, onion, celery and bay leaf; simmer, partially covered, for 20 minutes. Make Scallion Dumplings as shown.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccini to package directions. Drain in saucepan. Melt butter.
Add flour. Stir until thick.
Add milk.
Stir until thick.
Add cheese and bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly. Add salt and pepper. Stir. Take off heat and let stand 5 minutes. Pour over noodles and serve.

title: hershey's pie
directions: In microwave or double boiler, just barely get Hershey bars soft (do not melt).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in chocolate pie crust and refrigerate, at least 3 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put strips of bacon on top before baking.

title: brisket marinade
directions: Pour beer into roasting pan.
Mix tenderizer, pepper and onion in beer.
Mix bouillon in 2 cups hot water, when dissolved, pour into pan and add brisket.
Add hot water until brisket is nearly covered, add oil.
Cover with lid and put in refrigerator.
Let stand for 2 days, turning the brisket every 12 hours.
This will also work for other meats.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels with 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread on top of crust.
Combine water with Jell-O until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until almost set.
Pour mixture over cream cheese and put in refrigerator until set.

title: california peach-mint salsa
directions: Chop peach, about 2/3 cup, in a small bowl.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine. Spread in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat the egg whites and sugar stiff.
Pour beaten egg whites over crumbs. Spread evenly to edges. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. When cool, spread blueberries evenly. Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter and add chocolate chips.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Beat until smooth then add vanilla and pour into an 8 x 8 pan.
You can also add nuts.
The chocolate and butter can be melted in the microwave if you wish.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt oleo.
Add peanut butter, powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze 15 minutes.
Melt chips.
Can use 9 squares of almond bark chocolate and add the tablespoon of vegetable oil to chocolate mixture.
Pour over the peanut butter mixture.
Put in cool place.
Cut into squares.
Very good.
Makes 25 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and egg.
Stir in mashed bananas until blended together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter into 2 greased small bread pans.
Bake at 325° or 350° until done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange shortbread squares
directions: In small bowl, combine 2 cups flour, baking powder, and salt. In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy. At low speed, gradually stir in flour , mix until well blended. Chill 2 hours. Press dough into 13x9x2 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. In large bowl, beat eggs, remaining flour and sugar, juice and peel until light and fluffy. Pour over baked layer; Bake 30 minutes more.
Cool. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Carefully cut into 1 1/2 inch squares. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream-chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes. Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board. Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into rectangle, 14 x 10-inches.
Place dough in dish so edges are 1/2-inch up the side.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour evenly over dough.
Bake until edges are golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake ii
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add next 8 ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Add flour, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Bake pie shell in 400° oven.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and nutmeg in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sour cream.
Stir in egg yolks, raisins and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Pour into pie shell.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all well; shape into loaf.
Dot top with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 1 large cheese ball. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mandarin delight
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip, mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Pour box of jello into mixture. Stir and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Mix with squash and onions.
Mix melted oleo with stuffing; line casserole, saving some to garnish top.
Combine all other ingredients and pour into casserole.
Top with stuffing. Bake in 350° oven until bubbling and brown.

title: a good salad
directions: Add water to jello and dissolve.
Add 7-Up.
Let thicken.
Add drained pineapple (save juice).
Mix bananas, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Spread on jello.
Mix together 1 cup pineapple juice, sugar, egg and cornstarch.
Cook this until it thickens.
Cool.
Whip whipping cream and add it to the cooked mixture.
Spread over top of jello.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: homemade grape-nuts
directions: Measure all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Then bake in pans like cake until good and brown.
When cool, crumble and dry, then grind it.
Can be eaten without drying, like cake with fruit and milk.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
hamburger
meat with pepper and onion.
Pour off grease.
Add
tomato
paste, water, tomatoes and tomato sauce, then
oregano, parsley, garlic salt and mushrooms.	Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: no bake cherry or blueberry cheese cake
directions: In a bowl, beat the cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into pie crust and chill 2 to 4 hours.
When ready to serve, put pie filling on top.

title: apple food cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs, and sugar.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add alternately with the 3 cups of apples.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Pour in a greased and floured tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: smooshy cake
directions: Tear up cake into small pieces and put into a large bowl. Boil water for jello as directed.
Do not add the cold water. Dissolve jello in boiling water and add frozen strawberries, then put into bowl with the cake.
Blend all ingredients together with wooden spoon.
Put in jello mold and freeze for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add the sugar, flour, corn syrup and butter.
Beat until blended.
Cover bottom of pie shell with pecans.
Pour syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until the center is firm, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Serve with unsweetened whipped cream if desired.

title: chicken and macaroni au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat; blend in flour, cream cheese and seasonings together.
Gradually add bouillon and milk, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Combine with other ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes (uncovered).

title: barbecue sauce no. 1
directions: Mix.
Good on chicken or flank steak.
Should marinate meat in sauce overnight or several hours.

title: lemon supreme pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk, whipped topping and lemonade; mix well.
Pour mixture into crust and refrigerate until set. Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage until it loses its pink color, then drain.
Mix sausage, Bisquick and cheese in bowl.
Make into small balls.
If mixture is too dry, add 3 to 4 tablespoons of water.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Add Prego sauce and mushrooms.
Bring to a simmer for 15 minutes. Cook noodles in salt water until limp.
Then drain.
Place noodles in large baking pan and mix together hamburger mixture.
Pour tomato juice over noodles.
Use entire can.
Do not mix in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and bake 15 minutes.

title: kapusniak - sauerkraut soup
directions: Cook meat in water until well done.
Add onion, sauerkraut juice and sugar.
Beat egg, flour, milk and cream.
Add to soup and bring to boiling point.
Serve with potatoes or dumplings.

title: instant cappuccino
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in air tight container.

title: nissua
directions: Scald milk and butter in saucepan.
Pour over sugar and dissolve.
Mix yeast and water.
Add to slightly cooled sugar mixture.
Stir in cardamon, eggs and salt.
Add to this mixture flour, 2 cups at a time.
Cover and let rise.
Pour onto well floured surface.
Fold and knead.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Upon removing from oven, rub top of loaf with butter.
Sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar.
Cool.
Makes 3 to 4 loaves.

title: caesar salad(mix at last minute)
directions: Rub bowl with crushed garlic clove. Break romaine into bite-size pieces to turn into the bowl.
Pour over oil and mix to coat well.
Break eggs into salad and mix.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and mix thoroughly.
Add anchovies and cheese. Mix again. Add the croutons and mix well.
Taste.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and serve at once.

title: chicken barbecue special
directions: Prepare chicken.
Rinse.
Cut slits around edges so it won't curl up.
Sprinkle salt and pepper in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon poultry seasoning and 1/4 teaspoon Mexene chili powder in bottom of pan.
Lay chicken on it.
Sprinkle salt and pepper and remaining 1/4 teaspoon poultry seasoning and Mexene chili powder over top.
Put in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then turn over for 15 more minutes.
Put all other ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir with a fork.
When chicken has baked 30 minutes, turn over and spoon on top.
Wait 10 minutes; turn and spoon remainder of sauce on top.
Let it bake 10 more minutes.

title: apple-raisin slaw
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples; toss well.
Mix in raisins and cabbage.
Add mayonnaise.
Toss and arrange lettuce lined bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: chuck wagon pot roast
directions: Remove most of fried meat from pan.
Pour off drippings.
Pour can of soup into pan, stir well to loosen browned bits.
Add 1/4 cup water and 2 to 4 tablespoons meat drippings, as desired. Heat, stir often.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Especially good with beef, chicken, ham and pork.

title: easy caramel-pecan rolls
directions: Mix pecans, 2/3 cup brown sugar, the corn syrup, and 1/4 cup margarine in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2 inches; spread to cover bottom of pan.
Set aside.
Stir baking mix and milk until dough forms; beat 20 strokes. Turn onto surface dusted with baking mix; gently roll in baking mix to coat.
Shape into ball; knead 10 times.
Roll dough into rectangle, 15 x 9 inches; spread 2 Tbsp. margarine.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and the cinnamon; sprinkle over rectangle.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side. Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal well.
Cut into twelve 1-1/4 inch slices.
Arrange cut sides down in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Immediately invert on heatproof serving plate.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Carefully separate rolls.
Serve warm.
Yield:
12 rolls.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening thoroughly. Add egg and blend well. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add with vanilla extract to first mixture; blend thoroughly. Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, depending on thickness of cookie. If desired, press cookies with fork before baking.

title: hadasha's broiled fish
directions: Put fish in flat pan or broiler pan.
Baste completely with lemon juice.
Set aside approximately 15 minutes prior to cooking, then add fresh thyme (sprinkle a lot all over fish).
Sprinkle paprika to taste; salt and pepper to taste or seasoned salt. Place other ingredients on top of fish; place dabs of margarine on fish.
Put in broiler; do not turn fish.
Brown to golden brown or color desired, brushing or basting with juices from fish periodically.
Add a tiny bit of water to fish.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread in dish and sprinkle with 1/2 package taco seasoning on top.
Cut up about 2 cups lettuce on top of sour cream-cream cheese mixture.
Top that with a layer of green onions.
Then a layer of black olives.
Then tomatoes, chopped (about 2 tomatoes).
Then cover top with grated sharp Cheddar cheese (about 12 ounces) and remainder of taco seasoning package.

title: chewy lemon wafers
directions: Place egg whites in a medium bowl; beat until foamy.
Add next 8 ingredients; stir mixture until smooth.

title: crunch swiss and ham appetizers
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll the balls in the cereal.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Sprinkle sugar over top of salad.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: biba's pesto
directions: Blend in food processor or blender first four ingredients. After blending, add the Parmesan cheese.
Serve tossed with pasta!

title: catherine's clear gazpacho soup
directions: Mix all together.
Add more lime or salt to taste.
Serve thoroughly chilled.
Garnish with fresh dill if desired.

title: barbecued salmon(number of servings: 4)
directions: Rinse salmon. Pat dry with paper towels. Combine lemon juice and soy sauce in shallow glass dish. Add salmon. Let stand at cool room temperature no more than 15 to 20 minutes, turning several times. Remove salmon from marinade. Discard marinade. Season lightly with salt and pepper.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in sheet pan, according to directions.
Bring pineapple and sugar to boil, then pour over cake.
Let cool.
Mix pudding by directions and pour over cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.

title: oven candied sweet potatoes
directions: Prepare
& boil

whole sweet potatoes in water until just tender. Cool. Drain, peel and cut into 1/2 inch slices. In a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish layer half each of potatoes, brown sugar, butter, and salt. Repeat layer.

title: pineapple ambrosia
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss gently to coat all fruit.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion.
Cook shells, drain.
Add spices and tomato sauce.
Cook 1 hour.
Layer shells and sausage mixture and some cheese, ending with cheese.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon-garlic broiled shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp and set aside.
In a small saucepan, cook garlic in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer or a baking pan.
Pour sauce over shrimp.
Broil about 4 inches from heat source for 6 to 8 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Baste once during broiling with sauce in pan.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with crusty bread to absorb sauce.
Serves 4.

title: elf candy
directions: Heat to a rolling boil, and boil one minute.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Add 2 1/2 cups oatmeal and mix well.
Quickly drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool and eat.
Coconut may be substituted for oatmeal.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in hot butter or margarine until golden, about 10 minutes.
Add water, salt, pepper, dill weed and bouillon cube.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and simmer

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake at 300° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: hell's canyon cake
directions: Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: all occasion whipping cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour heavily a Bundt cake pan.
Mix Crisco and sugar, one cup at a time, until well mixed.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add 1 cup cake flour, alternating with a little whipping cream to keep moistened.
Repeat until all flour and cream have been added.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Top will have a firm crust.
Check for doneness by inserting a knife until it comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool. Invert on serving plate and sprinkle or sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine buttermilk and baking soda; stir until baking soda is dissolved.
Add flour to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk and beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla, black walnuts and coconut.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites; beat until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter crunch
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes; remove and stir.
Cool and store in covered container in refrigerator.
Good topping on ice cream and puddings.

title: reindeer fodder
directions: Melt chocolate and oil in microwave.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Pour melted chocolate over mixture and mix and stir. Spread mixture over wax paper on cookie sheet.
Let set for awhile, then break into pieces and store in air tight container.

title: one bowl cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in water.
Add cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Mix well and chill, stirring once or twice before salad fully sets.
Prepare this in a dish that can be sealed or covered.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease 9-inch cast-iron skillet or 9-inch square pan; place in oven to heat.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crackers and oleo to form crust layer.
Blend together pudding, milk and ice cream.
Spread evenly over Ritz crust; frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed Heath bars on top.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and reserve 1/2 cup.
Press remaining cookies into 9 x 13-inch pan. Drizzle melted butter over the crushed cookies.
Chill.
Place cream cheese and sugar into a deep bowl. Mix at medium speed until creamy.
Blend in one cup of Cool Whip. Spread over cookie crumbs.
Chill.

title: creamy taco
directions: Brown meat and onion, adding 3/4 cup water after it has browned.
(You may have to add a little cooking oil to brown the meat and onion.
If you do, be sure and drain before adding the taco seasoning and water.)
Add remaining ingredients except Fritos or Doritos.
Cook over medium/low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot or it can be cooked in a crock-pot on low until ready to serve.
Serves as follows:
Place Fritos or Doritos on plate and cover with desired amount of Creamy Taco mixture.
Serves 8.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef or turkey in skillet seasoned with seasoned salt Drain off any fat.
Put remaining ingredients with meat in a large pot and simmer for about 2 hours.
Best served 2nd day after spices have had a chance to soak in beans and meat.
Can be thickened with flour, if desired.
Add hot sauce to taste, if desired. 1 pound of dried pinto beans can be substituted but they must be thick with very little juice.
Also you must increase the chili powder and cumin to 3 Tbsp. each.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat frypan with Pam on low heat.
Fry 1 clove garlic, chopped up, just until brown.
Fry cut up chicken until cooked.
About halfway through cooking, add cut up onion and mushrooms.
Once these brown, pour wine over all.
Let boil a couple of seconds. Turn off; set aside.
In large pan, put in tomato paste mixed with water to desired thickness.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix chicken with wine and onion; stir.
Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: parmesan popovers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Place well-greased muffin pans in 425° oven for 3 minutes.
Remove pans from oven.
Fill each muffin cup 3/4 full with batter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 18 to 20 minutes longer or until popovers are firm. Serve immediately.

title: marvel's tasty oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream sugar
and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in oats, buttermilk and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, soda, nutmeg and nuts.
Combine flour and butter mixtures; stir until moistened.
Fold in fruit or chocolate chips.
Fill cups to 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: creole mac
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Saute green peppers and onions in margarine until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Combine milk and egg yolks; gradually stir into sugar mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and
boils.
Boil and stir one minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly and chill.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and make into balls.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Add butter, lemon rind, juice and egg yolks.
Stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick; cool.
Fold in sour cream. Spoon into baked pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: crab roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on tortillas and roll up and refrigerate.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Slice and place on serving tray.

title: rocky road cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 12-inch pizza pan with foil.
Grease foil.
Press cookie dough into bottom of foil-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle evenly with peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips. Drizzle with caramel topping.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Remove foil from pizza pan.
Cut into wedges or squares.
(May substitute your cookie recipe.)
Makes 16 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil separately.
Pour over salad ingredients.
Mix well and marinate overnight or longer.
Flavor improves after 24 hours.
Keeps well.

title: brown beans and sausage
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain and cook in water until tender.
Cook sausage and onion together until sausage is well done.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Mash 1 1/2 cups of beans and return to vessel cooked in.
Add sausage-onion mixture and cook together until well mixed.
(Sugar can cause sticking if too high heat is used.)

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer: Mix together crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; cool.

title: audrey aul's homemade bread
directions: Mix liquids and yeast.
Add dry ingredients.
Knead until stiff.
Let rise until double in thickness.
Put into pans.
Bake for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cha-han(fried rice)
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden.
Stir in rice.
Heat through and add remaining ingredients.
For a creamy effect, break an egg over the rice and mix it well into the rice.
The Japanese add any vegetable or cooked meat to Cha-Han, as they are available. Serves 4 to 5.

title: sourdough hot cakes
directions: Before baking time, remove 1 cup batter, to replenish that used.
To remaining batter in bowl, add soda, eggs, shortening and sugar.
Mix well and bake on lightly greased, hot griddle.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (sugar, brown sugar, water, corn syrup, vinegar and salt).
Cook to hard ball stage (260°).
Add 3/4 cup butter and stir until melted.
Pour over popcorn and coat. Add peanuts, marshmallows and M&M's.
Mix well.
Put in greased mold.
When cool, take out.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from fruit, reserving only pineapple juice.
Mix dry pudding mix with pineapple juice.
Add fruit.
Top with drained cherries.
Chill.

title: cheesy crostini
directions: Stir together Swiss cheese and next 3 ingredients.
Spread 1 side of each bread slice evenly with cheese mixture; sprinkle with diced bell peppers.
Place bread slices on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.
Top with olive slices.
Serve immediately.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Don't open oven while baking.
Wrap in plastic wrap as soon as it is removed from oven.
When cool, put in freezer. Makes 3 large loaf pans.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add well beaten eggs and mix well.
Mix and sift flour, salt and baking powder and add to the first mixture.
Add orange juice and orange rind and mix to a smooth dough.
Chill.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain well on paper towels.
Combine with remaining ingredients in large bowl, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover; chill in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fake steak
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Shape into balls. Wrap with bacon, securing with toothpicks.
Brown on all sides in skillet.
Pour off drippings.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a bowl with a lid.
Season as needed.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with syrup; gradually add milk and egg and stir to blend, then add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° until done in center.
Serves 6.

title: fat-free fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in small saucepan.
Add small amount of milk into dry ingredients until moistened.
Then add rest of milk. Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: praline eggnog pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix unflavored gelatine with sugar.
Blend in egg yolks, beaten with 1 cup eggnog.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining eggnog, liqueur, rum and vanilla. Pour into large bowl and chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into prepared crust; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with cranberry sauce.

title: eva's cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage in blender.
Mix sugar and salad dressing well. Add salt, pepper and vinegar to cabbage and mix well.

title: frosted rice krispy treats(kid's recipe)
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup and cook until boiling.
Stir as it cooks.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips and melt.
Spread over top.
Great recipe for kids to help with.

title: oreo lasagna
directions: Mix crushed Oreo cookies and melted oleo. Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut ice cream into 6 slices and place on top of Oreos. Cover with fudge sauce and then cool. Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with nuts. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: pea soup
directions: Pour 6 cups of water into a cooking pot. Wash peas and add to the water. Add beef bouillon and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour over medium heat. While cooking the peas, cut up all veggies into small pieces and add to the pea mixture. Cook for another 1/2 hour. Mash all the veggies in the soup. Cut the kielbasa into small pieces and add to soup. Cook for an additional 1/2 hour. Let soup stand for 24 hours in refrigerator. Heat before serving and enjoy! Serves 6.

title: mom's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and vegetables in just enough water to cover, until done. Remove chicken and cool; reserve broth.
Remove skin from chicken and discard.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.

title: island pork chops
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Brown pork chops on both sides. Remove from pan and keep warm.
Melt butter in same skillet.
Add green onion and garlic.
Saute until soft.
Stir in flour, curry powder, chicken broth, salt, pepper and pineapple with juice. Bring mixture to a boil.
Return pork chops to pan.
Cover. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add snow peas.
Cook for a few minutes until tender.

title: cheddar-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems and set aside.
Brush mushroom caps with 2 tablespoons melted butter; place in lightly buttered shallow baking pan.
Set aside.
Saute onion and chopped stems in 1/4 cup melted butter over medium heat until tender. Remove from heat and add breadcrumbs and remaining ingredients. Spoon cheese mixture into caps.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts and mushrooms are thoroughly heated.

title: christmas punch
directions: Use perk coffeepot.
Place all liquids after mixing in coffee maker.
Place the cinnamon sticks in coffee basket.
Let liquids perk through for approximately 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: janie's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; bone chicken and remove skin.
Break into small pieces.
Put into large baking dish.
Add vegetables (drained), soups and spices.
Add enough broth to smooth it out, but not too much.

title: salted nut rolls
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and 2/3 cup melted butter.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Cook in crock-pot
1 hour on high.
(Four to 6 hours on low or simmer.)

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Press and crunch Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken over this.
Then mix thoroughly the remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Then grate 1/2 moon cheese and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomatoes in red wine
directions: Slice tomatoes; mix in bowl with onion and celery.
Cover with red wine and chill overnight.
Garnish with celery leaves and serve.

title: applesauce cookies(diabetic)
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and remaining spices. Add raisins and oats.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and blend.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Pour in large mixing bowl.
Add oil, eggs, milk and spices.
Beat batter well before adding nuts and prunes.
Stir well and put cake in round tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Shake milk and flour together in a jar with lid until smooth (no lumps). Place this mixture in top of double boiler and mix and stir constantly over low heat until thick and creamy. Set aside to cool. To creamy mixture, add Crisco, butter and sugar. Beat all by mixer at high speed until fluffy. Add vanilla and continue beating (the longer you beat, the whiter it gets). As you're beating, test for sugar granules. When nice and smooth with no sugar granules, frost your cake.

title: hawaiian or banana bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and bananas.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add flour, salt, soda and pecans.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until brown.

title: bahama mamas(make in 1 gallon ice tea jar)
directions: Make up juices; add rum and grenadine.

title: sweet onion salad
directions: *Vidalia, Texas Sweet or Florida Sweet.

title: sour cream patties
directions: Combine all but corn flakes thoroughly.
Gently stir slightly crushed corn flakes into meat mixture.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Shape into patties.
Broil 4 inches from heat about 6 minutes on each side.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper toweling, crumble and set aside.
Drain fat from pan, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
In the bacon drippings, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, water, rice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, chili powder, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until rice is done and most of the liquid is absorbed. Top with the crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix lemonade, limeade, water, syrup and rum. Put in freezer 2 days before serving. Stir every 4 hours first day.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn; set aside.
Preheat oven to 250°.

title: standard pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening (do not use hands) until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle water evenly over surface.
Stir with fork until all dry particles are moistened.
Shape into a ball; divide into 2 parts. Roll each into a 12-inch circle.
Fit into 9-inch pie plate and crimp edges.
Yields 2 crusts for 9-inch pies or for pie with top crust.

title: vegetable-stuffed mushrooms(microwave)
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems and chop; set caps aside.

title: elegant party cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions using either a 15 x 10 or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: danish christmas rice pudding
directions: Put milk, rice, sugar and salt into the top of a double boiler.
Cover and cook until rice is soft and thick (about 1 1/2 hours), stirring occasionally.
Cool completely then add vanilla, chopped almonds and whole almond.
Whip whipping cream until stiff.
Carefully stir into rice mixture.
Heat cherry pie filling and serve on top.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Cut in margarine.
Add beaten eggs mixed with buttermilk. Fold in raisins.
Bake in 2 small greased loaf pans at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Or bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion in margarine and mix with pimento.
Boil chicken until done and take off the bone.
Cook rice and chicken broth very dry.
Make sauce of soup, onion and milk.
Put layers of chicken and rice.
Pour sauce over.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chess cake
directions: Heat first two ingredients on low heat.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients in order.
Flour two 8-inch square pans that have been greased.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut and roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Yields 32 pieces.

title: david stanley's famous pudding cake
directions: Make cake by instructions on box.
Make pudding while cake is baking.
Remove cake from pan and put on a platter.
Open can of pineapple and pour juice all over top of cake (not sides).
Spread pudding evenly across the top of cake.
Spread Cool Whip over the entire cake, including sides.
Chill and serve.

title: apple glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, butter, brown sugar and applesauce; heat and serve.
Season cold cooked carrots as suggested in the recipe; place in baking dish.
Cover; bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry pineapple crisp
directions: Stir cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple together and pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix with hands, yellow cake mix and 1 stick margarine until blended well.
Pour cake mixture on top of pie filling mixture in baking dish.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with coconut, then top with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: tuna salad sandwiches
directions: Mix tuna, mayonnaise, and pickle relish.
Spread on toasted bread.
Top with lettuce, cheese, and tomatoes.

title: apple pizza
directions: Make pastry according to package directions.
Roll dough into one 14-inch round and place on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Turn under edges and flute.
Core unpeeled apples and slice fairly thin.
Fill pie shell, arranging them in circles and overlapping. Stir together flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter; stir in nuts.
Sprinkle topping over the apples.
Bake on lowest oven rack at 450° for 25 minutes, or until apples are tender. Slice in wedges and serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ham) with mixer until smooth. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on a tortilla.
Add a layer of ham.
Top with another tortilla, cream cheese, ham, etc.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
The top tortilla should be plain.
Should be enough tortillas to make 2 stacks, 5 layers each.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into small, pie-shape wedges.

title: chicken in a packet(4 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Tear off 2 pieces of foil the size of a cookie sheet.
Place 1 piece of the foil on a cookie sheet. Spoon half of the barbecue sauce on the center of the foil.
Layer the chicken, green and red peppers and potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with the black pepper.
Top with the remaining barbecue sauce.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 3 quarts.
Simple and delicious.

title: salt pickles
directions: Mix water, salt and vinegar together.
Put cucumbers in vinegar mixture.
Pickles are ready to eat in three days.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken; leave broth/stock in pan.
Remove skin and bone from cooked chicken.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken and broth.
Cook over medium heat about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter and egg.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts and chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Contains 90 calories per cookie.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and pour into greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.
Don't put cold glass into oven.

title: fruit cake christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Stir in sifted flour and salt.
Beat egg white and fold into mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts (pecans only).
Add finely chopped fruit.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of batter 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes; do not overbake if you like chewy cookies.

title: dill pickle potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel and cube potatoes; place in a large bowl.
Add the eggs, celery, onions and pickles.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, pickle juice, mustard, celery seed, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour over potato mixture; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Serve in a lettuce lined bowl if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crisp croutons in skillet in 2 tablespoons olive oil with split garlic clove.
Stir in anchovy paste.
Rub a wooden salad bowl with split garlic clove. Place bite sized chilled and dry romaine leaves in bowl. Scatter with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with remaining oil and cheese. Add croutons. Pour over greens, the egg.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce and lemon.
Toss lightly.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Parboil chicken for 15 minutes in salted water. Drain and cool.
Mix flour, egg and enough milk to make a thick paste. Add 1/2 cup beer. Dip chicken in batter and deep fry until done, turning occasionally.

title: squash pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on hot greased griddle like pancake.
Don't get griddle too hot.
Barely salt after cooking.
Serve immediately!

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with nonstick vegetable spray; set aside.
Cream together the cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla and sugar.
Roll out 1 can of rolls into pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over rolls.
Roll out other can of rolls on top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk, and vanilla together in a microwavable bowl until partially blended. Put butter stick on top of ingredients and microwave for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth. Blend in nuts. Put into buttered pan (10 x 6 x 2 inches). Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator or 20 to 30 minutes in freezer.

title: hillbilly cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese. Fold in thawed Cool Whip. Put in pie crust and top with pie filling. Chill.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: Put seasoning and 1 teaspoon flour over chicken.
Melt some butter in pan.
Add chicken, turn around until half done, then add onion.
Continue until all the meat is white, not brown.
Add wine and if necessary some more seasoning.
Reduce heat and let steam a few minutes, then add heavy cream and keep on smallest flame a few minutes and serve.

title: country ham with coca-cola gravy
directions: Trim fat off of ham slices and melt it in a large heated frying pan.
Add the ham slices and fry slowly until fatty edges are soft and brown.
Turn and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, punch holes in top and pour Eagle Brand milk over top and let cool.
Pour caramel topping over cake, then spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with crushed candy bars.
Refrigerate.
Can be prepared night before.
Best if prepared ahead of time.

title: key lime pie
directions: Heat to a boil the first 7 ingredients.
Cool until thickened. When cool add very well beaten egg whites.
Fill precooked pie shell. Top with whipped cream and chocolate sprills.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add soup, sauce, chilies and milk to beef and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Line baking dish (greased) with layer of tortillas, meat sauce and cheese.
Then repeat, making a layer of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbling.

title: harvest pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease
a
x
5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sift together
flour,
baking
powder, salt, baking soda and spices.
Combine eggs, milk, oil, pumpkin and brown sugar. Stir in cereal and
raisins.
Add dry ingredients all at once. Stir just until moistened.
Turn
into
pan.
Bake
to
60 minutes or until tester
inserted
in
center comes out clean. Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: texas bbq sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, garlic and celery.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in water, catsup, vinegar, worcestershire sauce, bay leaves and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove a little of the sauce and mix with chili powder, then add to the rest of the sauce.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil, add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Mix cocoa and coloring together and add vinegar.
Mix well and add to creamed mixture.
Beat hard and add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and beat until blended. Pour into 3 layer pans and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together all listed ingredients in a bowl and serve with potato chips

title: mustard sauce
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, vinegar and egg in small saucepan. Blend well and cook over low heat, stirring constantly. Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 3/4 cup.

title: refrigerated strawberry jam
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine strawberries and Sucaryl in saucepan.
Place over high heat and stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin; return to heat and continue to cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in ascorbic acid powder and food coloring, if necessary.
Ladle into clean half pint jars; seal.
Store in fridge.
Makes 2 1/2 pint jars.
Contains 5 calories per tablespoon.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place into ungreased pan.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter; add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well. Pat into 19 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Beat eggs; add remaining butter and confectioners sugar.
Beat 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas and bury in sugar mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over banana layer.
Spread Cool Whip on this.
Cut up cherries, sprinkle on top.
Lastly, sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine seafood and celery in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over seafood and celery.
Toss.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken tropical
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Coat chicken.
Brown in oil.
When golden brown, add pineapple, raisins and almonds.
Cook in oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken from sauce.
Put chicken in oven to crisp.
Serve sauce as gravy.

title: roasted conchs
directions: Build a roaring fire.
After fire burns down, place conch, foot-up so water can be added as needed during roasting.
Roast until conch shell crumbles.
After roasting, pull conch meat from shell; peel black off.
Cut into small chunks.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat all together well. Put in large pie pan. Bake 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crunchy caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan over low heat; stir frequently until smooth.
Pour mixture over combined cereals; toss until well coated.
With hands slightly moistened with water, press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle with melted chocolate chips.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon and remove skin and bones.
Combine salmon, pepper, onion, bread crumbs, eggs and 1/2 of the tomato sauce. Mix well and put in greased 8 x 4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread remaining tomato sauce on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together green beans and cream of mushroom and chicken soup.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into a baking dish.
Lay Durkee onion rings on top.
Cook at 350° until onion rings are brown, about 10 minutes, then cover with foil and cook for another 20 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom and chicken soup

title: aunt connie's corn souffle
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Gradually add milk and bring to boiling point, don't scald).
Add corn and 2 egg yolks, beaten thick.
Season and cook for 10 minutes.
Fold in
egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Spoon into unbuttered baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: captain's soup
directions: Cook chopped onion in a small amount of oil until yellow and soft.
Add ground beef and cook, stirring, until chunks are gone and all pink has left meat.
Add juice and soups; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until about boiling.
Then add the frozen vegetables and simmer for about 10 minutes until vegetables are done.
(Note:
This is very thick.)

title: spaghetti soup
directions: Brown sausage in 3 or 4-quart pan.
Drain.
Remove; set aside. Add green pepper, onion and mushrooms to pan and saute until tender.
Add meat and all ingredients except cheese and spaghetti. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Add to soup. Top bowls with cheese or add to soup.

title: iron skillet roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place roast in iron skillet.
Pour soup and water over roast; sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil. Place in preheated oven and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn oven off but leave roast in oven until oven is completely cool. To warm, place skillet on top of stove on medium heat.

title: mexican pralines
directions: In two quart saucepan, combine sugars, corn syrup, butter or margarine and water.
Bring to boil.
Add nuts and continue cooking over medium heat until candy reaches soft ball stage or 238°.
Remove from heat and stir rapidly until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Quickly drop candy from teaspoon onto waxed paper and allow to harden.
Makes about 24 pralines.

title: dutch coleslaw
directions: Heat the first 6 ingredients to boil.
Add some of mix to beaten eggs and then add this to the rest of the vinegar mixture. Cook until mix thickens and boils.
Remove from heat and add milk or cream.
Pour, while hot, over shredded cabbage and onions. Chill and serve.
Serves 18.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; cream until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Stir flour into creamed mixture; add oats and candy. Roll into 1 inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 350° oven about 10 or 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Stew giblets separately in boiler.
Chop, then use saved broth for gravy.
Take some of broth in cup; add enough cornstarch to make paste.
Add to gravy broth.
Boil about 3 eggs.
Grate fine and add to gravy after it is finished or just slice the eggs.
Do not get gravy too thick.

title: biscuits
directions: Baking biscuits only takes about 10 minutes.
Sift flour, then add baking powder, sugar and blend in shortening.
Add buttermilk until a dough.
Remember to flour surface before pouring dough out to knead and roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits out and put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: bavarian cream pie
directions: Soak gelatine for 5 minutes in 1/4 cup milk.
Heat 1 cup milk in a double boiler.
Add gelatine mixture.
Stir into this mixture 2 egg yolks, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
When cool, add stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Put in crust and top with grated sweet chocolate.
Let set in refrigerator.
Makes two large pies.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt together.
Fold in the fruits and pecans.
Put in cupcake holders in muffin pans and freeze.

title: chicken in a pot(crock-pot)
directions: Put carrots, onions, and celery in bottom of Crock-Pot.
Add whole chicken.
Top with salt and pepper and liquid of choice. Sprinkle basil over top.
Cover and cook on Low 8-10 hours (High: 3-1/2 - 5 hours, using 1 c. liquid).
Remove chicken and vegetables with a spatula and serve.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add cold water, then berries.
Chill in dish until set.

title: mike's favorite banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, alternate layers of wafers and bananas.
Save 10 or 12 wafers for topping.
In saucepan, combine flour, sugars, milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Mix well and pour over wafers and bananas.
Add remaining wafers to top.

title: wacky chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour.
Mixture will be very runny.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.

title: onion casserole
directions: Spray a frypan with Pam and add a pat of light margarine. Saute onions on low heat.
Do not brown.
Put a layer of onions (1/2 of them) in 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Repeat with a layer of onions and cover with more crackers.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top and bake, uncovered, at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Squeeze out as much moisture from spinach as possible; set aside.
In wide frying pan over medium heat, melt butter; add onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring until soft.
In a large bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in onion mixture, bread crumbs, soup, 2 tablespoons cheese, pepper, basil, oregano and spinach.
Turn into a well-greased 9-inch square baking pan; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 35 minutes or until edges are beginning to brown.
Serve warm or let cool.
Serves 8.

title: pecan rolls
directions: In
heavy
10-inch ovenproof skillet, bring brown sugar, corn syrup
and
butter
to
boil
over
medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce
heat,
simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat, cool
slightly.
Arrange
pecans
flat
side up in skillet.
On lightly floured surface roll dough into 16 x 12-inch rectangle. Sprinkle with
cinnamon sugar.
Roll up tight from 1 long side, pinch seam to seal.
With sharp knife, cut into 16 even slices. Arrange
1/2-inch
apart
in skillet.
Cover.
Let rise in warm spot until
doubled.
Bake in center of preheated 375° oven for 15 to
minutes
until golden brown.
Carefully invert onto large serving
dish.
Let skillet remain 2 minutes for caramel to drain down.
Makes 16.

title: rainbow ice cream cake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Divide into thirds; place in medium size bowls.
Sprinkle strawberry gelatin over one bowl of cake; lime over the second and orange over the third.
Toss each lightly with fork until cake is well coated with gelatin.
Place strawberry cake pieces in bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Spoon strawberries over cake; spread 1/3 of ice cream over strawberries. Repeat layers with lime cake pieces, blueberries and ice cream; orange cake pieces, oranges and ice cream.
Freeze until firm. Unmold on a chilled dessert plate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Boil potatoes, sauerkraut and onion for 20 minutes.
If you are using the egg add it here.
Shake flour into water to thicken soup.
Season
with
oleo
or
drippings.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add sour cream.
Turn off heat.

title: oven fried kentucky chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and chicken, in bag, shaking to mix well.
Spray with Pam or grease jelly roll pan. Rinse chicken and pat off excess water.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture to coat.
Arrange, skin side up, on prepared pan.
Brush skin side only with butter until distributed evenly.
Bake, uncovered, without turning at 350° for 1 hour or golden brown.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Beat eggs, buttermilk, flour, salt and pepper.
Soak fryer pieces while preparing cooking oil in 3-inch deep pan (skillet), temperature on medium-high.
Dip pieces in flour and roll over and over until coating is thick.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain and place on paper towels.
Try this recipe with cubed steak.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together with your hands or a pastry cutter until blended, but not oily.
Divide the crumbs into two parts.
Stir into one half of the crumbs the following ingredients which have been combined and beaten: soda, egg and buttermilk or sour milk.
Place the batter in a deep, greased, ovenproof 9-inch pie plate.

title: sinful pie
directions: Soften ice cream and mix with Cool Whip and Kahlua.
Fill pie shell and freeze for several hours.
Serve with hot fudge sauce.

title: sun pickles
directions: Rinse a 1 gallon jar with boiling water.
Layer pickles, dill and garlic in jar
and pack tightly.
Mix water, vinegar and salt and pour over pickles (cold).
Seal tightly.
Place in a sunny spot, turning jar over once a day.
After 8 days, check and see if there is any white spots in pickles; if so, leave in sun until spots disappear.
Refrigerate and eat.
Holds 6 to 8 weeks.

title: crab louis
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients.
Add crab meat and celery; toss together.
Cover and chill completely.
Serve in avocado shells or lettuce cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour over potatoes the onion, chicken soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream.
Top with margarine mixed with corn flake crumbs. Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Squeeze all moisture from spinach.
Mix 1 1/2 c. Mozzarella cheese with sour cream and 2 Tbsp. of Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and pour into greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips or toasted pita strips.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion and bacon; mix well. Pour into large casserole dish.
Arrange onion slices on top of beans and bacon on top of onion.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until bacon looks done and casserole is brown around edges.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk together.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Boil until soft ball stage.
(I test in cold water.
You can use a candy thermometer.)
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, marshmallow and peanut butter.
Beat until all is smooth. Put into a buttered dish, cool and cut into squares.

title: hummus
directions: When all finely chopped and mixed, add sesame paste (will stiffen mix).
Stir, cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables and pita bread.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 3-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: town house chicken
directions: Stew chicken until tender and let cool in broth.
Bone and cut in pieces.
Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup (undiluted), and sour cream together.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Crush crackers coarsely and pour the melted butter over crackers and stir with fork.
Add celery seed and sprinkle cracker mixture over chicken and bake uncovered until bubbly, approximately 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dill green tomatoes
directions: You will need 12 to 14 pint jars.

title: ellen's oven fried chicken
directions: Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll chicken in Bisquick mixture.
Cover cookie sheet with foil; spray with Mazola.
Melt butter; spread evenly.
Lay chicken, skin side down, in pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes more.
If chicken starts to brown too much, turn oven down to 375° or 350°.
Also turn periodically.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent roll dough flat in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool in pan.

title: fruit kuchen
directions: Cream margarine and sugar with electric mixer.	Add egg and vanilla
(lower
speed
on	mixer when adding dry ingredients). Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.	Pat dough while distributing it	in
well-greased
and
lightly	floured
10 x 10-inch
pan. Cover
with
ready	mix
pie
fruit
(peaches, cherries or pineapple).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: turnip surprise
directions: Peel and dice turnips.
Cover with cold water and soda.
Bring to boil; drain and rinse well.
Cover with more salt.
Cook until almost tender.
Drain.
Mix sugar, flour, onion, celery salt and cheese.
Add to turnips and mix.
Put in 9 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Pour milk over it.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: potato rivel soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water.
Bring to a boil.
Mix egg, flour, salt and pepper with a fork until pieces are about pea size to make rivels.
Add rivels to boiling potatoes and stir immediately.
Cook for about 8 minutes.
Add milk and butter. Continue stirring so rivels don't stick.
Simmer for about 5 to 10 minutes while stirring.

title: coffee frosting
directions: Beat well and let stand a few minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix well
and bake in Bundt pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 275°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cream cheese, horseradish, onions, Worcestershire sauce and crab meat.
Spread in a 3-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with Captains Wafers.
Serves 8.

title: santa's snow delight
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and butter; spread evenly in bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
