Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix 1 container of Cool Whip and cream cheese; whip until smooth.
Spread over vanilla wafer crust.
Spread strawberries and pineapple over cream cheese mixture.
Cover with 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Spread bananas and 1/2 package walnuts over Cool Whip.
Cover with 1/2 container Cool Whip and sprinkle remaining walnuts on top.
Chill.

title: granny cleo's pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in 2 layers.
Turn out 1 layer and cover with 1/2 large can of crushed pineapple and juice.
Drizzle on Icing, then place second layer on top.
Spoon on remainder of pineapple and juice.
Top with icing and chill.

title: velvet corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, corn, onion, parsley, whipping cream, bread, cheese, Tabasco sauce and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place baking dish in a large pan filled with water reaching 2/3 up side of baking dish.
Place on rack of oven that's below middle of oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake until top cracks open and knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: company cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Trim with reserved crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until just set.
Cool.
Chill well for 4 or 5 hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer the spinach, eggs, bacon, sliced mushrooms and lettuce. Blend together the mayonnaise and sour cream.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar and paprika.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: one bowl yogurt pound cake
directions: Mix until thoroughly blended.
Pour into lightly oiled Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for one hour.
May be glazed with 1 cup confectioners sugar and 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Pour over cooled cake.

title: jello frozen pops
directions: Dissolve Jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water. Pour into paper cups.
Freeze 2 hours until sticks or spoons stand up.
Freeze 8 hours until firm.
Once frozen store in plastic bag.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Mix together well.
Put in a well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: so easy lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 inch pan. With lightly floured fingers, press dough evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 1 1/2 quart loaf pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add flour gradually.
Stir in vanilla, potato chips and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: 7-up red satin punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
Prepare 7-Up ice cubes or 7-Up ring.
At serving time, combine cranberry and apple juice in punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled 7-Up.
Add "ice cubes" or "ice ring." Makes 35 punch cup servings.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Boil gizzards until tender (salt and pepper to taste).
Drain, saving broth.
Dice gizzards.
Put back into broth.
Dice eggs; add to broth.
Add sage.
Bring to boil.
Mix flour with water. Beat together until all lumps are dissolved.
Add to broth, stirring consistently so it won't stick and scorch.
Reduce heat and simmer until you've reached desired consistency.
Add more water if too thick.

title: homemade eagle brand sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put in blender and process until smooth.
Makes 14 ounces. Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: tuna roll-ups
directions: Roll bread dough out on floured board.
Brush with melted butter.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly over dough. Roll up like a jelly roll and cut into 8 slices.

title: devils food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding boiling water last.
Mix will be runny.
Bake at 400° until it starts to rise then turn back to 350° to 375° until done.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in milk in saucepan.
Stir in frosting mix.
Spread in buttered pan.
Cool. Cut in squares.

title: beef 'n tater bake
directions: Combine hamburg, bread crumbs, egg, onion, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Pat meat into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain excess fat.
Combine mashed potatoes and shredded cheese and spread over meat; top with 1/4 cup shredded cheese and bake for 20 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix bacon, cheese, onion and 1 egg at a time.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Stir in shrimp and crab last.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: cottage cheese pan rolls
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Combine cottage cheese and egg in a blender; whirl until smooth.
In a large bowl, stir together baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and 3 1/4 cups of the flour.
Work butter into flour mixture with your fingers until no large particles remain.
Stir in cheese mixture and yeast.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Mix all ingredients together and place into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Mix with other ingredients and top with grated cheese.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Bring to a boil and add 5 pounds extra lean hamburger (raw). Stir and cook on medium or low heat until grease comes to top. Cool and remove grease.
Freezes well.

title: chicken breasts with feta cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease large baking dish.
Flatten chicken breasts.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Work until smooth. Spread cheese mixture evenly onto chicken breasts.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Brush with olive oil and bake for 40 minutes.

title: golden nut crunch
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix nuts and margarine in medium bowl.
Add cheese, garlic powder, oregano and celery salt; toss.
Spread in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cereal.
Cool.
Store in airtight jar.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add to milk.
Add beaten eggs, butter and vanilla flavoring.
Bring to a boil, stirring until thickened and pour into baked pie shell.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually adding Eagle milk and egg yolks and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Combine egg whites to sugar and salt and add this to cream cheese mix; folding gently and then fill 24 muffin papers with one wafer each and top with cheese mix until 1/4-inch from the top.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes.
Top with fruit and serve.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter; beat in eggs.
Add sugar and stir in pineapple. Fold bread cubes into mixture.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss well and season to taste.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs, vanilla, soda and salt.
Add flour; mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mini meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add ground beef.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once.
Serve with wooden picks.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese with sugar.
Add flavorings.
Add whipped whipping cream.
Spoon into pie crust and add pie filling on top.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well the cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Place part of mixture in pan and cover with pie filling.
Cover with rest of cake mixture.
Top with combined flour, sugar, oleo, cinnamon and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, measure and then add baking powder and salt; sift again.
Stir vanilla into milk; add alternately with dry ingredients, beating well each time.
Stir in walnuts to distribute evenly through batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve plain or with icing.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat
vinegar,	oil and sugar to
boiling
point.
Pour over combined sauerkraut, celery, green pepper and onion.
Let stand (covered) in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy crumb crust
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar.
Mix in butter and press firmly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
For unbaked crust, chill one hour before filling.
For baked crust, bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool thoroughly before filling.

title: liver sausage party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except liver sausage, into paste.
Mash sausage; blend into paste.
Shape and chill.
Blend cream cheese. Add milk.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Frost ball.
Garnish with olives.
Serve with crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside. Crush Oreo cookies and set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Combine with cream mixture.
Put dirt layer (cookies) on bottom of 8-inch flowerpot lined with an instant coffee filter.
Alternate approximately 5 layers, ending with dirt layer (cookies) on top. Refrigerate.
Add flours.
Mix in gummy worms, if desired, and serve with a trowel.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, add sugar and cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead and place in refrigerator overnight; covered. Cut off amount needed.
Make out as biscuits, but do not allow to rise before baking.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour;
add to eggs and sour cream.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Add raisins; stir well, pour into pie shell.
Put in
icebox
when cool.	Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased glass dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: chart house mud pie
directions: Crush wafers and add butter.
Mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with soft coffee ice cream.
Put into freezer until ice cream is firm.
Top with cold fudge sauce.
(It helps to place the fudge sauce in freezer for a time to make spreading easier.) Store in freezer approximately 10 hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Shred remaining ham and roll on outside ball.
Serve 6 to 8 people.

title: grandma cookies
directions: Mix melted butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then gradually add flour and oatmeal.
Add coconut and chocolate chips.
Then roll into a ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole (cheesy)
directions: Boil cabbage, onion and salt to wilt.
Drain and place half of cabbage in buttered dish; cover with layer of 1/3 cup cheese.
Top with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Repeat all 3 layers.
Dot with butter.
Pour in milk to cover crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10-15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding(great with fried or baked chicken)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, milk and salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.
Add drained corn; mix.
Pour into greased dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chips and nuts. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Beat together eggs and milk. Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage, milk, eggs and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until mixture is lightly brown and filling is set.

title: salted peanut bars
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds, in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.

title: oooblick(is it liquid or is it solid?)
directions: Place water in bowl, add about 1/2 cup cornstarch; mix.
Add rest of cornstarch slowly until the mixture becomes very hard to stir.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
If raw peanuts are used, add at this point.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir.
If roasted peanuts are used, add at this point. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add the butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Most peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup will be very hot.
Add the baking soda; gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into small pieces.

title: lime salad
directions: Add gelatin and lemon juice to hot water and stir until dissolved.
Stir in creamed cheese until dissolved.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: rowena's curry chicken
directions: Coat chicken and brown in oil; remove.
In drippings over medium heat, cook garlic, onions, green pepper, celery, curry and salt for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and raisins.
Add chicken. Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Brown almonds in butter, shaking skillet occasionally.
Sprinkle almonds and parsley over chicken.
Serve with hot rice or noodles.

title: wild rice-chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions.
Meanwhile, cook onion and celery in butter till tender.

Stir in soup, sour cream, wine and curry. Stir in chicken and cooked rice; turn into a 2-quart casserole or a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Stir before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup pizza sauce.
Mix balance of ingredients together and place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, pressing firmly.
Place on a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour reserved pizza sauce over top and bake 30 more minutes.
Sprinkle reserved cheese over top and bake 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Remove from pan with pancake turner so cheese on top will not be disturbed.

title: party pizza appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds.
Spread with mixture.
Put pizzas on cookie sheet and freeze.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in plastic bags.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind pork and ham twice.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: nikki's favorite barbecue sauce
directions: Double for large amounts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased, shallow baking dish, 10 x 6 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour lemon juice and syrup over apples.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is consistency of coarse corn meal.
Lightly stir in cheese.
Top apples with this mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until apples are very tender.
Serve warm with or without cream.

title: silly slime
directions: You'll need a measuring cup, 2 glasses, a spoon, 2 bowls, scissors and a straw.

title: hungarian goo-lauch
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together until brown. Cook macaroni noodles; drain shells and set aside. Add garlic salt, ketchup, tomatoes, sugar, red pepper and salt to hamburger. Add cooked macaroni shells to mixture.

title: chunk pickles(old fashion)
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers into 1-inch pieces.
Soak 3 days in brine made by dissolving 2 cups salt and a gallon of cool water. Drain and soak cucumbers 3 days in clear water (do not change the water).
Drain.

title: shrimp and scallop saute
directions: Melt butter with olive oil in heavy, large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Increase heat to high.
Add sliced mushrooms; saute until just beginning to soften, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste; stir for 30 seconds.
Add dry white wine and lemon juice; bring to boil.
Add shrimp and sliced green onions; stir 1 minute.
Add scallops; stir until shrimp and scallops are cooked through, about 3 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley.
Serve immediately over a bed of rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and margarine in heavy container. Bring to a full boil, but do not allow mixture to continue to boil long.
Beat eggs; gradually add hot syrup mixture, being sure to stir eggs rapidly while adding.
Add pecans, vanilla and salt; mix.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(This recipe doubled will make 3 pies.)

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Pour into 2 large well-greased and sugared (mix cinnamon and sugar) loaf pans. You can sprinkle some extra cinnamon and sugar on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: turkey vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onion, celery and thyme until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add soups and milk; stir until smooth.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish combine turkey, cooked vegetables and pepper; add soup mixture, stirring gently to mix.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of broccoli soup
Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: farmer brownies
directions: Mix cocoa into hot water. Stir in butter. Allow to cool. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into cocoa mixture.
Add eggs. Beat in buttermilk and vanilla. Add nuts. Spread in buttered pan, 17 x 12. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Frost with chocolate powdered sugar frosting.

title: rocky road buttermilk cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl; mix well.
Bring water, oil and margarine to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix real well.
Mix buttermilk, soda and eggs and add to cake mixture. Beat well again.
Bake in 12 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.
Check every 5 minutes as gets done quick and will end up dry.
Ice with Rocky Road Icing.
This cake is moist and makes a good pot luck dessert.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate morsels until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Measure out 1/4 cup soup. Combine with hamburger, crumbs, onion, parsley and egg. Shape into 16 meatballs 1 1/2-inch in diameter. Brown in butter in skillet. Blend remaining soup with water and pour over browned meatballs. Cook ingredients over low heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: louisiana strawberry bread
directions: In one bowl, mix first five ingredients.
In second bowl, mix the rest.
Combine mixes.
Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate dream icing
directions: Chop chocolate into small pieces; set aside.
Combine cream and sugar in large 3-quart heavy saucepan.
Stir with wooden spoon over medium heat until mixture boils (full boil).
Reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until melted.
Stir in butter until melted.
Add vanilla.
Place pan in ice water to chill.
Stir frequently until cool.
Then beat with wooden spoon until very thick and spreadable.
Yield:
frosting for a 2 layer cake.
I like to put a thin amount between layers and put 1/2 cup raspberry jam on it between layers.
A very tasty surprise.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients, press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Chill, then cut into bars.

title: white bean soup
directions: Cube slices of ham and onion and saute in melted butter. Add cream, water, beans, chicken bouillon and pepper; bring to a boil. Lower heat to simmer and cook 1 hour. Stir occasionally. Mash the beans in the soup. Cook another 20 minutes and serve.

title: husband's delight pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Cool.
Put into pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: alfredo style noodles
directions: Cook noodles in water (no salt).
Drain and return to pot. Add remaining ingredients and toss well to mix.
Transfer to warm platter.

title: 1-2-3 patties
directions: Mix all ingredients; fry in oil.
Make mushroom and tomato soup gravy.
Serve separately and add to hot patties just before serving.
(Otherwise patties will become a loaf!) Makes good hamburgers, too!

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Drain pineapple really good and mix in bowl with milk, lemon and Cool Whip.
Pour in 2 pie shells.
Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with cherries and serve.

title: mexicalli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Fry onions in margarine for 10 minutes. Add chili beans, corn and tomatoes; mix well.
Pour into 10 x 8-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin dough according to package directions.
Stir cheese into dough.
Spoon dough around edges of baking dish.
Bake at 350°.

title: granny's blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together milk and egg.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add 2 cups of blueberries and spoon into muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: butter rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Add vanilla and sugar. Roll out biscuits.
Put mixture in biscuits. Roll up.
Put in pan.
Cover with milk. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fig strawberry jam
directions: Pour sugar over figs.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Add jello and cook for 12 more minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: italian beef sandwiches(a great crock pot recipe)
directions: Drain pepperoncinis, reserving liquid.
Remove and discard stems of peppers; set aside.
Cut roast into large chunks; place 1/2 of meat in 5 quart slow cooker.
Add water.
In small bowl, combine all seasonings.
Sprinkle half of seasonings over beef. Place peppers over seasoning, add reserved liquid.
Top with remaining meat and seasonings.
Place onion slices on top.
Cook on low 8 to 9 hours.
Shred beef with fork.
Serve beef, peppers, and onion on roll with mayonnaise.

title: quick beer biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put the desired size biscuits on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for about 8 to 12 minutes (slightly brown on top).
Makes about 10 biscuits.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Put in large bowl, and make hole in center.
In different bowl beat egg whites and put in cream of tartar.
Put all other ingredients in hole of dry ingredients, and mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Use a tube pan.
Bake 1 hour. at 350°.

title: refrigerator nut crispies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; mix well.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda; stir into creamed mixture.
Combine well.
Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 2 portions; wrap each portion in waxed paper.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased sheets, 2 inches apart.
Yields about 3 dozen when sliced 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.

title: stir-fried chicken & rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat 2 Tbsp. of the corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli, carrots, walnuts and garlic. Stir fry 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Add remaining 2 Tbsp. corn oil to skillet.
Add chicken and stir fry 1 minute or until chicken turns white.
Add soy sauce, sherry, ginger and sugar; stir fry for 2 minutes.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon.
Add broth and green onion to skillet; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and vegetable mixture.
Remove from heat and let stand and cover about 5 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and shortening.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, soda, salt, and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough into balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: southern fried okra
directions: Sprinkle the okra in a large bowl with salt and pepper as desired. Mix flour with okra and stir gently until well coated. Heat cooking oil until hot and then put okra in it. There should be enough oil so that the okra will cook as individual pieces. Cook 10 to 12 minutes on medium-high until light brown. I dip mine out with a large cooking spoon (with holes) and drain in a metal colander.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix pumpkin pie mix, eggs and milk in bowl.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13 baking pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top of pumpkin mixture, spread evenly over pumpkin.
Pour melted butter over cake then sprinkle nuts on top of butter.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool completely, spread Cool Whip over top and serve. 16 to 20 servings.

title: pork chops and sauce
directions: Heat frying pan.
Add oil.
Salt meat and coat in flour; place in frying pan.
Brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and drain all fat from pan.
Put meat back into pan; spoon mushroom soup over top and add pepper.
Cover with a tight fitting lid.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and boil in a little water until tender.
Mix together flour, salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with flour mixture.
Heat milk and margarine together until margarine melts.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake a few minutes longer until lightly browned.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cheese, milk and salt.
Mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Mix lightly; chill several hours or overnight.
Add additional salad dressing just before serving, if desired.
Serve on lettuce covered platter. Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add all the vegetables and season with salt and pepper over medium heat.
Pour tomato sauce and water over ingredients and let simmer for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours until vegetables are tender.

title: granny nichol's chocolate pie
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.	Mix egg yolks and small amount of	milk
together.
Gradually whisk in remaining milk. Add melted butter
and
vanilla.
Add
dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into
pie
shells.	Bake
at
425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco oil, margarine and sugar. Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and all dry ingredients. Add milk, a little at a time. Mix well for about 15 minutes. Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon lamb with mint
directions: Preheat broiler.
Lightly spray a broiler pan with vegetable oil spray.
Pour oil into a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and saute.
Stir in water, lemon juice and pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Sprinkle mint over mixture and simmer about 10 minutes.
Cover and set aside.

title: steak barbara anne
directions: Rinse steak and salt and pepper slightly.
Place sliced onions and bell peppers evenly over steak.
In a small pan, heat mushroom soup with 1/2 can water until smooth.
Pour soup over steak and peeled potatoes (arrange potatoes around steak).
Bake until steak reaches your desired tenderness.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Soak in salt and beaten eggs for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain; roll in bread crumbs and brown in butter.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms and top with cheese. Baste with chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pesto
directions: Blend basil leaves, garlic and enough oil to process until liquified.
Remove from blender container to refrigerator or freezer bowl.
Add grated cheese and mix well.
Refrigerate (will keep 2 weeks) or freeze.
I use ice cube tray and transfer pesto cubes to plastic bag.
Remove 1 or 2 cubes when needed and thaw at room temperature.
Do not heat or cook.
Freeze without cheese.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in baking dish.
Spread creamed soup on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: In large skillet, saute chicken and onion in hot oil until chicken is no longer pink.
Add vegetables and saute 2 minutes longer.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in spinach and let cook 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot cooked fettuccine and top with cheese.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add vanilla, sugars and milk.
Pour into your 5-quart freezer container.

title: crepes suzette
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add milk.
Sift and mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to beaten eggs and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Cook in frying pan as follows.
Melt butter in pan, when melted, add a thin layer of mixture.
Turn mix when bubbles appear on top.
Cook like a pancake.

title: ravell's apple dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Wash and slice apples.
Dip in orange juice.
Drain and arrange on a plate for dip.

title: no cook macaroni and cheese
directions: Put in 8 x 8-inch greased casserole.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May add corned beef or other meat if desired.

title: oatmeal butter thins
directions: Mix all ingredients well; knead with hands and make small balls (size of nickle).
Roll in granulated sugar.
Roll flat with a glass on an ungreased pan and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: ham spread
directions: Grind in food processor.
Mix with enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Good for leftover ham.

title: hillbilly pot roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover the roast or bake in a cooking bag at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 5 people.
Can be served with noodles or mashed potatoes and carrots or any vegetable.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix milk and sugar.
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Add chopped dates and let dissolve.
Remove from heat and beat; add coconut and pecans.
Continue to beat until stiff.
Pour on a damp cloth and roll up.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop.
Brown stems in butter with onions, garlic, parsley, salt and oregano.
Stir in bread and cheese.
Spoon into caps.
Place stuffed side up.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a bowl, mix sour cream and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add raisins, about 1 cup.
Flour and grease pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: One day or up to 1 week ahead, rinse sauerkraut by running under cold water. Drain well. Dice red and green peppers.
In a large bowl, stir sauerkraut, peppers, cider vinegar, brown sugar and caraway seed until mixed.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with sliced tomatoes and/or grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple rum torte
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, 3/4 cup rum, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in 2/3 cup coconut. Pour into prepared 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Cut into 3 (10 x 5-inch) pieces.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Combine pudding mix, 3/4 cup pineapple, reserved juice and remaining rum.
Stir and fold in whipped topping.
Place 1 layer on plate, spread with topping mix.
Top with rest of pineapple. Repeat layers and cover with rest of coconut.

title: annie's great potatoes
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion and 3/4 part of cheese.
Add potatoes; mix together.
Put in flat baking dish.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, pudding & 1/2 the Cool Whip until thick. Layer crackers, pudding & banana. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large shallow roasting pan.
In heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Stir constantly while bringing to a boil, without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda. Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Remove from oven, spread onto foil.
Break apart as popcorn cools.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, egg yolks, pudding and sugar. Boil until thick.
Add chunk pineapple, marshmallows and bananas.

title: reese's chewy chocolate pan cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Gradually blend into creamed mixture. Stir in chips. Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until set. Cool completely; cut into bars.
Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix in order listed.
Put in graham cracker pie crusts (1 for a thick pie or 2 for thinner pies).
Chill about 6 hours before serving.

title: pork tenderloin in mustard seed sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Rub mixture over pork; place in a plastic bag and refrigerate 8 hours.
Place tenderloins on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of meat.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until thermometer registers 160°, basting every 10 minutes with wine.

title: grape-nuts roast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes. Bake in moderate oven for 40 minutes in greased bread tin. Serve with your favorite gravy.

title: cranberry - apple crisp
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cranberries, apples, sugar, cinnamon and 1 tablespoon of flour.
Transfer the mixture to a greased 6-cup shallow baking dish.

title: yummy chicken casserole
directions: Saute chopped celery and chopped onion.
Add flour, sugar, margarine, salt and pepper and chicken broth.
Cook and stir. Reduce heat.
Add peas, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay canned biscuits on top or drop biscuit mix by tablespoon on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover and bake 10 minutes until dumplings are done.

title: warm artichoke dip or spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into ovenproof dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, put the ice cream; spread it out. Put 1/2 of the crushed Oreo cookies over ice cream, then the whipped cream, spreading over the cookies. Spread with remaining cookies. If you want to use gummy worms, bury part of them in the cookies and let part stick out.

title: featherweight cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar until mixture is very light.
Mix flour alternately with milk to the first mixture.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten until stiff, but not dry.
Add vanilla.
Put batter into two greased layer pans.
Bake at 350°. Frost to taste.

title: cocoa pudding cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa powder, baking powder and salt.
Add the milk, oil and vanilla, mixing by hand until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Combine the brown sugar, 1/4 cup of cocoa powder and water and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch crescent rolls
directions: Separate dough.
Cut in half lengthwise to make 16 crescents. Beat yolk with water.
Brush on dough.
Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Roll up in crescent shape.
Brush with egg mixture.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in preheated 375° oven for 11 to 13 minutes or until brown.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine sugar, egg whites, and water in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water on medium heat and beat with beater until frosting forms soft peaks and holds its shape about 8-10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Frost cooled cake.
This is enough for top and sides of 2 layer cake.

title: lolly pops
directions: You will need 8 wooden skewers.

title: dad's favorite coconut macaroons
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly add sugar; beat 5 minutes. Fold in flour, baking powder and salt, then fold in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Drop onto greased and floured cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: peach spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Do not invert.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Blend all dry ingredients; stir in.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar. Pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze at least 1 hour. Slice and serve.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
To serve, use 2 or 3 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: almond pine cones
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often, until almonds just begin to turn color.
Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings. Mix well.
Cover; chill overnight.
Form into shapes of 2 pine cones.
Place on serving platter or cutting board.
Beginning at narrow end, press almonds at slight angle into cheese in rows until all is covered.
Garnish with artificial pine sprigs.
Add cheese spreader or knife to plate.
Serve with crackers.
Looks festive.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter, mix with cinnamon crisp graham cracker crumbs and press into pan to make crust.

title: honey raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch pans.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and soda; sift.
Add the raisins and cereal.
Mix, combine and stir in another bowl the eggs, buttermilk, honey and butter, then pour the egg mixture into dry ingredients and blend lightly.
Divide the bread dough between 2 pans.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Add milk and butter.
Bring to a slow boil over medium heat.
Cook for 2 minutes boiling rapidly; stir often.
Cook to soft ball stage, remove from heat, ad vanilla, beat until you can spread on cake.
You can make fudge from this recipe.
Pour in pan, let cool, and cut into squares.

title: green noodle and chicken casserole
directions: *All the pimentos do is make it look pretty.

title: nina's apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand.
Beat eggs and add oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt into egg mixture, alternating with apple mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Frost with Lemon Butter Frosting.

title: brownie fudge squares
directions: Combine butter and cocoa in small saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until butter melts.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and sugar in large bowl, beating well.
Add cocoa mixture, beating until just blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 16 x 11 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: berry custard pie
directions: Beat all ingredients well, except berries.
Place berries in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over berries and bake at 300° until it doesn't shake in middle.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips and nuts on top.
Last, a little white sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add taco mix while beef is cooking.
Black olives and avocado can be added to salad, if desired.

title: judy's cheesecake
directions: Blend softened cheese with sugar and flour. Beat until smooth. Add eggs and yolks, one by one. Beat until smooth. Add vanilla and cream. Blend well. Pour into greased spring-form pan. Place into preheated 450° oven. Bake for 10 minutes. Lower temperature to 250° and bake an additional hour. Cool. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Top with fresh berries, if desired.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: west virginia corn bread
directions: Beat the egg whites.
In another bowl, beat the egg yolks. Add the sugar and beat well.
Add the corn meal, milk and flour. Add the melted butter, beaten egg whites, baking powder and salt. Pour into a greased tin pan.
Bake in a 450° oven until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Cool.
Beat eggs and stir in cracker crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano, Tabasco, cheese and parsley.
Add chopped artichokes, blending well.
Then add onion mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Spread in a greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
May be frozen, thawed and reheated for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook beef and onion in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat until meat is browned and onions are tender, stirring until meat crumbles; drain.
Stir remaining ingredients into beef mixture; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon soup into bowls.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add chocolate syrup.
Beat well.
Measure salt, soda and flour together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and melted Hershey bars.
Bake in a greased, floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Cool in pan.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Wash berries, add water, oranges and raisins.
Cook until cranberries burst and are soft.
Add the sugar, stir until dissolved.
Skim, turn in nuts and chill in individual molds or put up in jars.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, beating well after each egg. Sift dry ingredients together in a separate bowl. Add food coloring to cake mixture. Alternately add milk, butter and flour to mixture in that order. Add vanilla and vinegar. Beat. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: make ahead chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients well in a large bowl that will allow stirring every few hours. Refrigerate overnight or several hours to allow macaroni to soften. Pour into casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apples rolls
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Stir well. Cook over medium
heat
until sugar dissolves. Stir in butter, set aside.

title: puppy chow
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 3 minutes, or until melted.
Add cereal, stirring to coat.
Pour into large paper bag. Add confectioners sugar; shake to coat.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 16 servings.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Blend together and put in ovenproof dish for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve with crackers.

title: scripture cake(king james version)
directions: Follow Solomon's prescription for making a good boy (Proverbs 23:14, first clause), and make a good cake.
Bake in a tube pan in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Oh, and one more thing.
If you give this cake as a gift, be sure to include a copy of the recipe.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and gradually add sugar. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients.
Use tops only of the broccoli (raw) and thinly sliced red onion.
Wish-Bone dressing is the best.

title: pickled beets
directions: Select young, tender beets: wash fresh beets.
Leave 2 inches of stem and boil 15 minutes in water to cover.
Make a syrup of the sugar, water, vinegar and spices.
Put beets in hot sterilized jars.
Pour hot vinegar over beets and seal.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the sugar, cornstarch and water until thick, then add the jello.
Cool slightly.
Add the strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook beef until brown and crumbles and turn into casserole. Layer peas over meat and celery over peas.
Mix soup, cream, onion, salt and pepper over celery.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375 ° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all these ingredients in a bowl and pour into uncooked pie shell and cook at 350° about 30 minutes.
Check, you will know when done.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar. Stir in reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth. Cook over medium heat. Add pineapple tidbits and meatballs. Serve from crock-pot.

title: pickled egg brine
directions: Boil eggs and peel.
In a saucepan, bring vinegar to a boil. Add remaining ingredients except eggs.
Cool.
Place in 2 quart jar.
Pour brine mixture over and seal.
Store in refrigerator. Do not eat for at least 2 weeks.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop on cookie sheet or bake in a greased pan, then cut into squares.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard without crust
directions: Mix sugar with Bisquick.
Add to eggs which have been beaten well.
Add milk, butter and flavoring.
Put in baking dish.
Cook at 300° until firm.

title: microwave all seasons rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart microproof casserole. Cover and place in oven. Cook on 100% power for 12 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: batter bread
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Sift corn meal and salt.
Add boiling water; stir until smooth.
Add egg mixture and melted butter.
Mix and pour into ungreased baking dish.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 25 minutes.

title: burger pizza
directions: Using your favorite biscuit dough, roll out dough.
Crumble beef over dough evenly.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Spread tomato sauce over top.
Add Swiss cheese; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Rub all together and wet with 3 eggs.
Let stand overnight or roll into cylinders and freeze.
Slice or roll thin to cut into shapes.
Bake at 325° until the edges begin to brown. Can divide and freeze.
I roll into cylinders to slice in rounds for any occasion.

title: grandma's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and salt.
Add beaten eggs and then vanilla, syrup and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon butter pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in a pan and add lemon juice. Coat pork chops with lemon/butter mixture. Season with salt and pepper and place in a 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until done.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture; let set overnight.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and run water through them. Then mix remaining ingredients and pour over beans; chill 24 hours.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add dry cake mix and mix well. Add flour and knead.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch dough down.
Roll out dough; sprinkle with cinnamon. Dot with margarine and put raisins or chopped nuts on top.
Roll up and cut.
Place in pan and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a thankful heart
directions: A thankful heart can always find something to make it glad. Complaining minds, alas for them, they evermore are sad.
He who can smile and overlook the griefs of each new day shall find abundant happiness where love's sweet angels play.

title: magic pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
While draining, put spices and vinegar in 1/2 gallon jar.
Add drained pickles.
Pour sugar on top of pickles (do not stir).
Close jar.
Let stand for 8 days.

title: maple butterscotch brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine first three ingredients.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add walnuts.
Spread on a 12 x 18-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
These are delicious.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat the vinegar, sugar, salt and celery salt.
Pour over the beets and onion.
Refrigerate mixture and serve cold.
Keeps very well.
(This is very good to take on picnics.)

title: vegetable oil crust
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Whisk flour and salt. Mix milk and vegetable oil. Pour oil mixture over dry ingredients and stir with fork until blended. Pat dough evenly over the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan or 9 1/2 or 10-inch
two piece tart pan. If making a pie, crimp or flute the edge. Thoroughly prick the sides and bottom with a fork. Bake until the crust is golden brown, 12 to 18 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and cook.
Drain.
Mix sausage with croutons. Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup of water.
Stir.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (may vary with ovens).

title: budget skillet dinner
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in large, heavy skillet until meat is lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, sugar and seasonings to meat mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Simmer over low heat 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as package directs; drain.
Add to meat and tomato mixture; heat thoroughly.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Combine jello in boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, mashed bananas and nuts. Put half in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Let chill until firm. Spread sour cream over mixture. Spoon remaining amount of mixture over sour cream.
Chill and serve.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: Melt margarine; add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Turn heat off and add lemon juice.
Mix all these ingredients well.
Do not let mixture boil after adding lemon juice.
(This is called "juice" hereafter.)
Dip chicken in juice, letting some drip off, then lay on grill.
(Can be done on gas grill, but we find an old-fashioned charcoal grill is best.)
Continue to dip and turn for about an hour or until chicken is done, depending on size of pieces.
Main thing is to dip and turn many times during the course of cooking to get more flavor throughout chicken.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on a cookie sheet.
Press together to form 1 large sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and both packets together.
Spread on top of cooled rolls.
Top with chopped veggies and press firmly. Chill 2 hours before serving.
Cut into squares, a bit messy, but good.
Serves a crowd.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount of salted water; drain.
Cook carrots and onions until tender.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix, soup and sour cream.
Gently fold in zucchini and 3 tablespoons margarine.
Pour into a greased casserole.

title: liver pat
directions: Mix livers, water, bouillon cube, onion and thyme in 1-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer uncovered until liver is done, about 15 minutes.
Cool mixture; drain and reserve 1/4 cup broth.
Mix liver, reserved broth and remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend smooth. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Makes 2 cups.

title: brisket in oven
directions: Trim brisket and season with salt, pepper, Tony's seasoning, garlic salt and red pepper.
Place brisket in a cooking bag.
Pour on top of brisket, mushroom steak sauce.
Place in oven and cook until tender.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Pour vanilla into 1 hole, vinegar into another and divide the oil into all 3 holes. Pour cold water over entire mixture.
Blend thoroughly with a fork.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, brown ground beef with onion and garlic. Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: italian style baked mushrooms
directions: Chop mushrooms in half or quarters, depending on size.
Put in large pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and drain immediately.
Saute garlic in oil.
Remove garlic when browned. Combine oil, mushrooms and rest of ingredients together in ovenproof dish.
Cook at 400° until bubbly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with rolled corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zesty corn and sausage sauté
directions: In skillet, brown meat; drain.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cool until tender-crisp.
Add tomatoes.
Cook over medium-high heat 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened, stirring frequently.
Add corn; heat through.

title: chicken breast with leeks
directions: Melt the butter in a microwave-safe dish by cooking on High for 45 seconds.
Wash the leeks well and slice the white parts very thinly, discarding the tough green parts.
Add the sliced leeks to the dish.
Put the chicken breasts on top.
Pour the wine around the chicken.
Place the tarragon leaves on the chicken.
Sprinkle on a little salt and pepper.
Microwave on High for 12 minutes, turning the dish at least once.
(If you bone the chicken, it will cook in less time.)
And, if you like, you can add a variety of other vegetables for color and taste, such as broccoli and cauliflowerets and carrots.
The sauce with the leeks is wonderful over a little freshly cooked rice.

title: germans sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture; beat well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whites.
Pour into 3 deep 8 or 9-inch layer pans, lined on bottoms with paper.
Bake in moderate oven on 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only.

title: noodles florentine
directions: Cook
noodles according to package directions and place in casserole.
Cook
spinach according to package directions; set aside.
Combine
melted butter,olive oil, garlic, nutmeg, pepper and
lemon
juice
and pour over spinach, tossing well. Now add spinach mixture and cheeses, reserving 1/4 cup of the Italian grated
cheese to the cooked noodles in the casserole. Toss lightly.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake for 5 minutes at 475° or until cheese is melted.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar, vanilla and water.
Sift flour and salt together and stir into mixture.
Add pecans and mix thoroughly, using portions about size of small walnuts.
Roll into crescent shaped cookies.
Bake in slow oven (325°) about 20 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Mix peaches and sugar together in blender.
Add peaches and sugar mixture to other ingredients; churn in ice cream freezer according to machine instructions. Makes 4 quarts.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place a layer of broken chips in 13-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining ingredients evenly over chips. Make sure you have plenty of liquids.
Add more broth or soup just to make sure chips won't be dry.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with lots of grated cheese.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 1 quart water.
For quick soak, bring beans and water to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Then continue with recipe.
Drain beans and measure liquid. Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
Place soaked beans, water and ham hock in kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add potato, onion, celery and garlic powder.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove ham hock and cut up meat.
Remove 1 cup beans and some liquid and puree in blender. Return meat and pureed beans.
Heat; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: raisin penuche icing
directions: Combine and bring to a full boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in 2 cups sifted powdered sugar until of velvety, spreading consistency.
Spread on cooked raisin-applesauce cake.

title: berry goody
directions: Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time is 10 minutes.
Peel banana and place in blender with juice concentrate and strawberries.
Blend at high speed 10 seconds.
Use spatula to scrape down sides of blender container.
Add yogurt and juice. Blend until smooth.
Pour into 6 glasses.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Follow instructions on bread dough package.

title: tennessee beef stew
directions: Mix all together
and pour into pan.
Cover with tight lid. Place in a 300° oven and bake 3 hours. Do not remove lid until ready to serve. It makes its own gravy.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes or cooked noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: First, cut biscuits into 1/4's.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon together and roll the biscuits in it.
Put them in a tube pan. (It does not matter how, just throw them together.)
Pour the brown sugar mixture and butter over the top of all of the biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Immediately turn the tube pan over and put the bread on a plate or a cake holder. Can serve cold or hot.

title: steak, or what?
directions: Pat ground beef evenly in bottom of medium casserole dish. Layer potatoes, onion and peas over top of beef.
Mix both cans of soup and water.
Pour over top of meat and vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Salt and pepper to taste after combining all ingredients.
Put into an oblong casserole; top with dry bread crumbs or toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared and left in refrigerator for 2 days before baking.
Do not put bread crumbs on until ready to bake.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Pour into well greased pie pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil syrup and sugar to 300°.
Remove from heat and add baking soda all at once.
Mix together and pour into 2 greased cookie sheets.
Do not touch until cooled.
Break into pieces and dip into chocolate.
I open a fresh box of soda to make this.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add 1/2 stick of butter and cream cheese.
Blend together.
Add seasonings and sour cream. Put into a greased shallow casserole and cover with dry herb stuffing.
Drizzle 1/2 stick of butter over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine all remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with or without
vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: squash crab casserole
directions: Saute seasoning in butter.
Add crab meat, crab boil, squash and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot upside-down cake
directions: Drain apricots.
Reserve syrup.
Add milk to syrup to make 2/3 cup.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, margarine and water. Spread in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Arrange apricots, cut side up, over coconut.

title: easy chicken n dumplings
directions: Boil chicken with celery and onion until done. Keep water level over top of chicken. Debone chicken.
(Save the broth.)
In Dutch oven, strain broth. Throw away the celery and onion. Add bouillon cubes. Heat until dissolved. Tear or cut up tortillas. Add to broth. Bring to a boil. Add chicken and cover pot.
Cook approximately 30 to 45 minutes until desired thickness of your "dumplings."
It'll thicken faster with lid off, but be careful as the tortillas soak up the broth!

title: cereal burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 4 or 5 patties. Brown on both sides in lightly greased skillet, turning once. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat and onion, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over corn chips and rice.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon and mash with a fork.
Mix with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish and salt.
Form into a ball while still in bowl.
Chill 3 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Brown beef and drain.
Stir in salt, beans, sauce and sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour into casserole.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 semicircles.
Place cut side down around edges.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until biscuits are brown.

title: sesame spareribs
directions: Roast pork, uncovered, on rack in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Mix soy sauce, wine, sesame seed, oil, sugar, red pepper and garlic in a saucepan; heat to boiling.
Mix cornstarch and cold water; gradually stir into sauce mixture.
Boil, stirring, for about 1 minute.
Brush ribs with sauce.
Roast, turning and basting, until done, about 45 minutes.

title: favorite baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve drippings; set bacon aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings; drain.
Combine onion mixture, crumbled bacon, beans, flour and the remaining ingredients in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab crostini
directions: * Could also use 4 large slices of Italian bread and make it a main dish.

title: catfish italiano
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip fillets in lemon juice, then coat both sides with crumb mixture. Place in shallow coated baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Bake uncovered in oven for 10 minutes.

title: pizzaburger loaf
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. Combine the beef, egg, bread crumbs, salt, oregano, basil and 1/2 cup prepared sauce.
Form meat mixture into free standing loaf and place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over. Arrange sliced Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: nana's banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour in top of double boiler.
Mix in egg yolks and milk.
Mix well and cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
On bottom of dish, put a small amount of custard.
Cover with wafers.
Top with sliced bananas.
Pour custard over bananas.
Makes about 3 layers, ending with custard.
Top with stiff egg whites.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes (optional).
Always slice bananas longways (Nana did).

title: banana split pie
directions: Line bottom of pie crust with bananas.
Cover with ice cream. Freeze 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from freezer.
Top with fudge sauce.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Top with whipped topping. Serves 8.

title: ground beef and lentils
directions: Saute onions, garlic (or powder) and ground beef; add 1 quart vegetable stock or water bouillon, lentils, rice, cumin, pepper and sugar.
Cover and simmer 1 hour until rice and lentils are tender and liquid is absorbed.
Add water if necessary.
Stir in vinegar and salt.
Serve with fried eggplant and yogurt or tossed salad and bread.

title: triple treat jello salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and lime Jell-O in 1 cup hot water for each. Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until medium done.
Rinse in cold water.
Arrange layers in bowl of carrots, green pepper and onion. Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Stir thoroughly until blended.
Pour marinade over carrot mixture.
Refrigerate until flavor is absorbed.
Drain to serve.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 big or 2 small pies.
Refrigerate.

title: onion boats
directions: Brown hamburger in a 10-inch skillet; drain off grease, if necessary, leaving 2 tablespoons in skillet.
Stir flour into hamburger.
Add onion soup and 1 soup can water to hamburger. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Cut rolls in half.
Butter and toast rolls.
Spoon onion and hamburger mixture over toasted rolls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no peep stew
directions: Mix all together and bake 3 hours at 325°.
Do not peep. Microwave 1 1/2 hours around 50.

title: confetti crab dip(microwave)
directions: Place cream cheese in a 1-quart casserole.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until softened. Stir well.
Stir in crabmeat, green onions, mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave at High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in pimiento and wine.
Sprinkle with chopped fresh chives.
Serve warm dip with assorted crackers.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water, butter, sugar and salt in a heavy pan; bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once, then beat with a woden spoon over low heat for 1 minute or until mixture leaves sides of pan and does not separate.
Remove from heat and continue beating about 2 minutes to cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at least 1 minute after each.
Paste will be light in color and will hold stiff peaks when spoon is lifted.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Place ice cream in the center of each cream puff. Top with chocolate sauce.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Wash and seed peppers.
Put half of the peppers and 3/4 cup vinegar in blender.
Remove from blender and repeat with other half.
Combine pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil 5 full minutes.
Add a few drops food coloring; remove from heat.
Add Certo; bring back to boil and boil 1 full minute. Skim jelly well.
Put into jars; cover with wax.
Store in cool place.

title: deep fried biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oil.
Then add oil.
Pour out on floured board.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Pinch small amount off and roll into biscuit and flatten out.
Drop into deep fryer.
Cook until golden brown.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all together well and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost cake.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, butter, 1 egg and nuts.
Pack and press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, 1 box powdered sugar and cream cheese with mixture. Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown (do not overbake).
Cool before slicing.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Mix all together, add more sugar to thicken or water to thin. Makes a lot.
Cut in half for two-layer cake.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Brown meat (very brown).
Add bell pepper and onion, chopped. Cook a little longer.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Stir well.
Bake all together in a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish (sprayed with Pam) at 300° for 1 hour.

title: party jello salad
directions: Drain the can of cherries and add water to make 2 cups.
Boil and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add sour cream and whip until smooth.
Carefully stir in cherries.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Turn out onto a plate and decorate with fresh cherries if desired.
Can have as a salad or a low-fat dessert.

title: tuna spread
directions: Pour boiling water over tuna fish, rinsing thoroughly.
Mix all with mixer.

title: cheese crackers with sesame seeds
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in cheese.
Cut in butter and work in cream to make smooth dough. Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut with canape cutters.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; brush with egg yolk mixed with 1 tablespoon water. Sprinkle with coarse salt or sesame seeds.
Bake for 12 minutes or until golden.
Yields 24.

title: honey mustard lobster with asparagus
directions: Cook lobster in boiling water 8 minutes.
Rinse with cold water.
Split and clean tails.
Cut into 3/8 inch slices; set aside.
Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Steam over boiling water 8 minutes; set aside.
Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk, mustard and honey.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chives.
Arrange spears and lobster slices on individual plates.
Spoon mustard sauce over and serve.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam broccoli until separated.
Beat eggs; add flour, cream, seasonings, baking powder and onion.
Mix well.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and pour in broccoli mixture.
Bake 35 minutes.
Allow mixture to set 6 to 8 minutes.
Cut into bite-size servings.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with the milk according to package directions. Add condensed milk. Fold in whipped topping.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of pudding, then a layer of bananas. Repeat. Top with vanilla wafers, if desired.

title: egg salad and bologna rolls
directions: Make Egg Salad:
In medium bowl, combine chopped eggs, green pepper, olives, mayonnaise, mustard and salt, mixing well.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: In a bowl, stir milk into soup.
Add chicken, half of the cheese and macaroni; mix well.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.

title: apple mallow yambake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss apples, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of apples and yams in 9-inch square baking pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 45 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows over yams and apples.
Broil until lightly brown.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Diagonally slice frankfurter in 6 pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients and franks.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours.
To serve, remove garlic clove, heat sauce and frankfurters.

title: banana icing
directions: Best over white or yellow cake prepared according to package and cooled (banana cake is too rich!).
Spread bananas over cooled cake.
Bring other ingredients to boil, just to thicken, then "ooze" cooked icing over bananas gently.

title: gramma's cardamon cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add flour, baking powder and cardamon.
Work in almonds.
Shape into long rolls about 2-inches in diameter.
Chill.
Using serrated knife, cut in slices 1/4-inch.
Set on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Will keep a month in a sealed can.

title: a delicious one dish meal
directions: Cut meat in 1/2-inch strips and brown in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Place in casserole dish.
(Do sausage and beef separately.)
Chop or slice onion and quarter green peppers.
Cook them 1 minute in shortening and place in casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in the boiling water.
Quarter potatoes.
Add all the remaining ingredients to the casserole dish and mix lightly. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until beef and potatoes are tender.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Add red cake coloring for pink effect.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix cheese, soup and sour cream.
Mix 1/2 with cubed chicken; set aside other half.
Spoon mixture into tortillas and roll up. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; cover completely with remaining cream mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes (will not brown).

title: date loaf
directions: Cook milk and sugar together in a 3-quart saucepan until it reaches 236° or will form a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Add dates and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts, salt and vanilla.
Let cool a few minutes and then beat until it thickens.
Form into a roll by hand, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in a damp cloth or waxed paper. Chill and slice.

title: royal hibernian soda bread
directions: Sift regular flour, sugar, soda and salt 3 or 4 times.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Cut margarine in until like fine crumbs. Beat eggs until frothy.
Mix with buttermilk and add gradually to dry ingredients.
Mix with fork until stiff dough is formed. Knead on floured board for 20 to 30 quick motions.
Divide into 2 balls.
Place well apart on greased cookie sheet.
Cut an "X" about 1/2-inch deep in top of each.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand about 30 minutes before serving for best flavor.
Slice in thick slices.

title: martha craig's macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Cook (boil) macaroni; drain.
Add the butter; melt thoroughly. In casserole dish, layer macaroni and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper all together; pour mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Sprinkle paprika over it.
Put in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: carolyn's quiche
directions: Combine the first six ingredients and pour into pie shells. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Flour chicken breasts and brown in skillet with small amount of butter.
When browned on both sides, layer chicken in casserole dish.
Combine soup, sour cream, water chestnuts and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle almonds over the top.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
The chicken breast casserole can be made the night before, refrigerated and then baked prior to serving.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, at medium speed, cream butter, sugar, eggs and orange peel until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion in heavy skillet.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef macaroni dinner
directions: Brown meat and onions in butter.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese.
Cook and drain elbow macaroni.
Save macaroni until last.
Cook all ingredients including meat and onions in frying pan for about 1 hour.
Mix elbow macaroni, meat mixture and cheese in a large serving dish.
Arrange triangles of cheese on top.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain. Cool carrots. Mix all ingredients and pour over carrots. Marinate 12 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package omitting the salt.
Drain and cool.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and pepper together to make a dressing.
Toss all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Shape in 15 one-inch balls.
Blend soup and chili powder.
Stir in 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boiling.
Add meat balls; cover and simmer gently 1 hour, stirring a few times.
Makes 5 servings.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour; stir until blended.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic and cook until tender.
Add crawfish tails, fat and water.
Cook 10 minutes, then cover.
Cook another 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper, green onions and parsley.
Cook on simmer until thickness desired.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put into 2 baked pie shells. Sprinkle coconut on top and garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes after it reaches full boil.
Then remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well until blended.
Spoon out on tray or wax paper.

title: olivien - a persian delight
directions: This is your favorite potato salad, only enriched by the chicken, sour cream and curry.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump into a 9 x 12-inch pan and spread the pineapple and pie filling.
Top with dry cake mix and dot with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked crab spread
directions: Combine in bowl and mix well.
Spoon into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Saute green peppers and onion in butter.
Mix peppers, onions, cream of chicken, tomatoes, and chicken together.
In a 9x13 pan, alternate layers (2 times), 1) tortillas, 2) sauce mix, 3) cheese.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 325°.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large dutch oven; Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and cook over medium heat 3-4 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and bring to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Stir in pecans, butter and vanilla. Remove from heat.
Continue stirring until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper. Let stand until firm.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in large skillet.
Cook egg for 1 minute until set, but moist.
Remove to plate and cut in 1-inch strips. In remaining tablespoon of oil, stir-fry green onions for 2 minutes.
Add rice, chicken, peas, soy sauce and ginger. Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Add egg.
Cook 1 minute.
Serves 6.

title: crunchy surprise bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, molasses, egg yolk and vanilla with spoon.
