Stir in flour and 1 cup chocolate morsels. Press dough in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour half of the mixture into Jell-O mold.
Freeze 15 minutes.
Spread sour cream over it.
Pour remaining mixture on top and chill.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound steak and cut into serving size pieces.
In heavy skillet, brown steak in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Stir often.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix condiments in bowl and stir well.
Add more if needed.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine in small bowl. Reserve 1/4 cup of mixture for topping.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: In large pot, combine beans and tomatoes.
Fry bacon; add onions and garlic.
Cook until well done.
Add to beans.
Add seasonings and water
Simmer one hour, stirring occasionally.
Add rice the last 1/2 hour.

title: potato dumplings (potet klub)
directions: Mix grated potato well with flour and salt.
They may turn dark, but that's okay.
Brown or cook meat and onion.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
If too soft, add more powdered sugar.
Roll into balls and dip in chocolate mixture which follows.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together; let set 15 minutes.
Roll into small balls and flatten with sugared glass bottom.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cooked creamy caesar-style dressing
directions: Combine oil and garlic in jar with tight-fitting lid. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Remove garlic.
Set aside.

title: stir-fry chicken-n-vegetables
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add carrots, peppers and onions.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove.
Add 1 tablespoon corn oil to skillet or wok. Stir in chicken and fry until chicken turns white.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Stir in stir-fry sauce mix.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Serve over boiled rice.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce cookies for diabetics
directions: Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sweetener.	Stir
soda into applesauce; add egg.
Combine with creamed
mixture.
Gradually
add sifted ingredients, blending together
well.
Stir
in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until browned lightly.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Bake in 9 x 2 x 13-inch pan. Bring sugar and cream to a boil and boil for a few minutes. Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows until melted.
Stir in coconut. Make holes in cake.
Pour over cake while hot.
Enjoy!

title: becky's spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Beat eggs well.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix.
Add cheese and finely chopped onion.
Squeeze all water out of spinach and add.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Wait until completely cooled to cut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Shape into ball.
Chill overnight.
If you wish to make a small cheese ball, use only 2 packages of cream cheese.

title: salmon loaf(4 servings - freezes well)
directions: Clean salmon of any bones and skin.
Flake in a bowl.
Add all other ingredients. Mix together well.
Pack into Pam-sprayed loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with cream sauce, salad and garlic bread.
Healthy and great.

title: orange brisket
directions: Season meat with salt, garlic salt and paprika.
Place onions in bottom of roasting pan; place meat on top.
Make sauce of remaining ingredients; pour over roast.
Let stand about 1 hour or do day before to marinate.
Roast at 350°, covered, for about 3 hours, basting time to time.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Slip off the peelings and slice lengthwise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Arrange in buttered bake dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, salt and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Add water and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate bits in saucepan.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch
pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Enjoy.

title: mom's chip dip
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.

title: hidden valley ranch party pinwheels
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut rolls into 1-inch slices.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart round glass baking dish.

title: oven baked fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Under cold running water, scrub potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into wedges.
In a plastic bag, mix Parmesan cheese with paprika.
Then add potato slices, a few at a time, into the bag.
Toss to coat potato wedges.
Spray a cookie sheet with nonstick spray and place wedges in a single layer. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until crisp.

title: panoche
directions: Combine first three ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Add butter and cook, stirring occasionally until 238° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add extract and nuts.
Beat until candy begins to thicken.
Turn into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: paul's poultry seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Store in a covered container. Sprinkle on any poultry to taste. Makes 4 teaspoons.

title: turkey corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish combine the pasta and 2/3 cup shredded cheese.
In medium bowl combine soup, sour cream, chili powder, garlic powder, corn, green onions and turkey.
Spread evenly over pasta mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Blend strawberries in blender.
Combine jello and water.
Add strawberries, jello mixture and Sweet 'N Low to Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: crab casserole
directions: Drain and cut crabmeat into chunks.
Dice half the bread into bottom of large buttered casserole.
Combine crab, mayonnaise, celery, green pepper, onion and salt.
Spread over diced bread. Dice remaining bread and place over crab mixture.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove and spoon mushroom soup over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 1 hour longer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion and Italian dressing; toss gently. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard and salt. Pour over potato mixture and toss gently.
Add celery, eggs and relish and toss gently.
Chill.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a good boil, then add top three ingredients.
Stir well, then drop on wax paper.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle salt on zucchini and let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse, drain and set aside.
Saute onion and butter.
Add zucchini and flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add cheese, seasonings and zucchini mixture.
Pour in shell. Place in oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with tossed salad.
Yum!

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger 4 minutes in microwave.
Stir once; drain and add other ingredients.
Return to microwave; cook 10 minutes.

title: sheet coconut cake
directions: Bake cake. While still hot, punch holes all over cake.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In large skillet, fry hash browns according to package directions; remove and set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs; add onion and green pepper.
Pour into same skillet; cook and stir until eggs are set.
Remove from heat.
Add hash browns and sausage; mix gently.
Place about 3/4 cup of filling on each tortilla and top with about 1/4 cup cheese.
Roll up and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with salsa if desired.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix lightly; refrigerate. Makes 6 servings. Use Kraft real mayonnaise.

title: cocktail party meatballs
directions: Combine beef, potato, egg and onion in large bowl and mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Form into small meatballs. Blend remaining ingredients in large saucepan over medium heat. Add meatballs to saucepan.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Transfer meatballs to chafing dish or fondue pot.
Skim excess fat from sauce and pour sauce over meatballs.
Serve warm.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: great-grandma's 1-2-3 shortbread cookies
directions: Soften butter (not to a liquid form though).
Mix butter and sugar (to a very smooth texture).
Add flour very slowly (this is the secret).
Drop on cookie sheets with teaspoon.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes on top rack, then 15 minutes on bottom rack.
Allow cookies to cool completely.
Sugar cookies with 10x in a baggie.

title: mexican sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Spoon over hamburger buns.
Delicious.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage.
Add onion, green pepper, and celery; set aside.
Bring water to a boil.
Add soup mix and rice to boiling water and boil for 7 minutes.
Add sausage and vegetable mix to soup and rice.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Add sliced almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fluff-n-stuff
directions: Drain pineapple.
Fold Snickers chunks, diced apples and pineapple into Cool Whip in a large mixing bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: sue's ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Save broth.

title: pickled beet relish
directions: Large beets wash, leaving 2 inch tops and the root tip. Put in large kettle, cover with water and boil until tender. Remove from stove and drain off hot water then cover with cold water. The skins will slip right off. Remove the root tips and tops. Cut into quarters ready for grinding. In another container, mix sugar, water, vinegar, salt, cloves and cinnamon. Stir and boil for one minute. Add the ground beets and bring to boil and simmer for 5 minutes more. Seal in hot sterilized canning jars and serve as you would pickled beets.

title: white icing
directions: Cream Crisco and dry ingredients.
Gradually add liquid alternately with sugar so icing will be creamy.

title: refreshing fruit slush
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Freeze overnight, or until firm.
Remove from freezer 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving. (Mixture should be slushy.)
Makes 3 quarts.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion over medium heat until bacon is crisp and onion is tender. Meanwhile, place beans in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Cook, uncovered for 8-10 minutes or until crisp-tender, drain well. Add to bacon mixture. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, toss to coat. Serve immediately.

title: spicy vegetable beef soup
directions: Saute onions with oil and garlic.
Brown beef and drain.
Add Rotel, Ragu, broth and frozen vegetables.
Bring to simmer and add sugar and season with salt & pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 min. or longer if desired.
Can add little water to thin.

title: onion dip
directions: Stir together ingredients, cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Stir before serving.

title: cheese buttons
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls (size of marbles).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° about 18 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour
boiling
water over rolled oats.
Add shortening; cool; add molasses and salt.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to
oatmeal
mixture.
Add flour, wheat germ, beating gradually. Turn
onto
floured
board
and knead until smooth looking.
Turn into
a
greased
bowl,
cover, leave in a warm place 1 hour
or until doubled in bulk.
Shape into 4 loaves; place in greased bread pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 50 minutes or until well browned. Yields 4 loaves.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Whisk together pudding mix and milk in a large bowl until thickened.
Whisk in sour cream; fold in 4 1/2 ounces whipped topping.
Layer half of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture in a 4-quart bowl.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Cover and chill.

title: pecan pumpkin pie(homemade with love)
directions: Stir together 1 slightly beaten egg, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and pie spice.
Spread over bottom of pie shell.
Combine 2 beaten eggs, corn syrup, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon over pumpkin mixture.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: yummy cream cheese blueberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and thickened.
Pour in crust and chill.
Chill at least 4 hours to set.
When set, decorate with pie filling.
Cherry pie filling is good also.

title: tiny apple turnovers
directions: Cook apples in a saucepan over low heat about 20 minutes or until tender.
Combine sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir into apples and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring often.
Set aside.
Combine 2 cups flour, salt, milk and 1/2 cup oil in a mixing bowl; stir with a fork until mixture forms a ball.
Divide mixture in half.
Roll each ball out on a lightly floured board to 1/8 inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Spoon about 3/4 teaspoon apple mixture on half of each pastry circle.
Moisten edges with water.
Fold in half and press with a fork to seal.
Fry turnovers in 1 inch of hot oil until lightly browned, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Yield: about 3 dozen turnovers.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325° in a tube pan or layer pans.

title: candied yams
directions: Put potatoes in a glass baking dish (drain most of the juice). Add butter.
Cover lightly with cinnamon.
Pour in syrup until bottom is covered, but not covered completely over potatoes.
Put in oven until it becomes a simmer for about 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and cover the potatoes with miniature marshmallows, about 1/2 bag.
Put back in oven, cook until marshmallows are golden brown.
Serve and enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick lime torte
directions: Lightly spray a small shallow glass dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle dish with half the crumbs.
Mix together egg yolks, lime juice, peel and sugar in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Stir occasionally until thick.
Set mixture off heat.
Cool and add yogurt and whipped cream to cooled lime mixture.
Pour over crumbs into dish.
Top with remaining crumbs. Cover and freeze until firm.
Serve cut into squares.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart glass bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients. Microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring well at 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Blend.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour onto a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Spread out thin.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: preacher's pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Salt and roll in flour.
Lightly brown both sides in 1/4 cup oil in electric skillet.
Add cut-up pepper and onion.
Pour in water and simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Delicious served over rice.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, cream of tartar, corn syrup, salt and water.
Cook until sugar dissolves.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Preheat
oven to 200°.	Blend thoroughly melted butter, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.	Combine all other ingredients
in
a	large
shallow	pan.
Pour
over the butter mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Bake for 2 hours, stirring well every 15 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese; let set.

Blend milk with pudding mix. Mix for 2 1/2 minutes then set aside for 1 minute. Add cheese mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Grate Oreos in bowl. Layer: cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding, cookies. Layer in large bowl or flowerpot or kid's summer plastic pail with shovel. Place in refrigerator to set.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon; combine remaining ingredients and press into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vicki's catfish stew
directions: Use a large cast-iron pot and place 4 or 5 strips of bacon in bottom.
Let it cook.
Leave bacon in bottom of pot, then start layering with fish pieces, sliced potatoes, sliced onions and salt and pepper.
Layer until pot is full.
Salt and pepper each layer. Add enough water to just about cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cut down to simmer and cook covered about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Serve with white bread or cornbread.

title: sausage-spinach macaroni
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease.
If link sausage, take out of casing and crumble well.
Put back in pan and add garlic, spinach and tomato sauce.
Cook on low until sauce and spinach are done and well blended.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except onion.
Put in bean pot, put onion in center of beans.
Cut up bacon and put on top of beans.
Bake 2 hours at 250° to 300°.

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Mix meal and water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
In meantime, have oven set for 375°.
When oven is hot, put about 3/4 cup of Crisco oil in iron skillet and put in oven.
When oil is hot, put batter in skillet.

When bread begins to cook and the grease begins to brown the meal (there will be a crust form on the outer edges), pour excess grease out and place back in oven until you can shake loose from pan, about 45 minutes cooking.

title: fish with lemon spinach
directions: Cook and stir onions and margarine until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk and instant bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Arrange fillets in an oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spoon spinach around fish; drizzle lemon juice over spinach.
Spoon sauce evenly onto fish and spinach.
Cook uncovered in a 350° oven until fish flakes with fork, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cabbage beef casserole(serves 6)
directions: Saute ground beef and onions in 5-quart saucepan until meat is lightly brown.
Drain off fat.
Remove from heat; put in a 3-quart casserole.
Pour rice over meat.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Pour beef broth and water over mixture; cover casserole and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
To serve, mix well.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl and put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix next 4 ingredients like pie crust and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Brown roast.
In crock-pot, put potatoes, carrots and onions. Place browned roast on top of vegetables.
Combine beef broth and seasonings.
Pour over roast and vegetables.
Cook 10 to 12 hours in crock-pot on low or 4 to 5 hours on high.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add syrup; mix well.
Add all other ingredients (except pie shells).
Add a dab of butter.
Sprinkle nuts with flour.
Bake 50 minutes at 300° in unbaked pie shell. Double all ingredients except use 5 eggs and it will make 3 pies.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Mix lard, flour, white sugar and brown sugar with forks or fingers to form crumbs.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs; set aside for topping.
Beat eggs, sour milk and baking soda together.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and also cinnamon, if you want.
Bake at 300° until a toothpick comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: cherry top cheese cake
directions: Spray 9x13 glass pan with Pam. Preheat oven to 300°. Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, oil and 1 egg (mixture will be crumbly).
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom of glass dish.
In same bowl, blend cream cheese, sugar, 3 eggs and reserved cake mixture.
Beat 1 min. at medium speed.
At low speed, add milk and flavorings until smooth. Pour into crust and bake at 300° for 45-55 mins. until center is firm.
When cool, top with pie filling. Chill before serving. Store in refrigerator or freezer, covered with foil.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar, mayonnaise, egg and vanilla in mixer bowl. Sift flour, salt, cocoa, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to mixture alternating with warm water.
Pour into floured and greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package.	Pour half into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add taco and chili seasonings.
Add beans, corn and water if needed.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Grease two 9 x 9-inch baking dishes.
Crumble 1/2 corn chips in bottom.
Pour mixture over chips and add rest of corn chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese over top.
Bake at 450° until cheese melts.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake about 8 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: lemon glazed sponge cake
directions: Combine egg whites and cream of tartar in large bowl.
Beat until soft mounds begin to form.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer or use rotary beater of flat wire whip.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar gradually by sprinkling 2 tablespoons at a time over whites and continuing to beat until stiff peaks form.
Do not underbeat. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and remaining sugar into small bowl.
Add egg yolks, water and lemon extract; beat with spoon until blended (about 75 strokes).

Fold egg yolk mixture carefully into stiffly beaten egg whites, using about 30 foldover strokes. (To fold, cut whites down through mixture with a large spoon, flat wire whip or rubber scraper; lift up and fold over.
Do not stir or beat.)

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook one minute after boiling.
Cool to lukewarm and beat.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients up well.
Stir egg into the mixture. Add enough buttermilk until the batter is pancake consistency.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order.
Combine salad dressing and sugar and pour over vegetables.
May refrigerate overnight or 8 hours. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir before serving.
May add peas and celery, if desired.

title: philly 3-step cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Mix crumbs and butter; press into 8-inch square baking pan that has been lined with foil.
Pour batter over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Cut into bars.
Makes 16.

title: coconut cream pie(quick and delicious)
directions: Stir and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: santa's sweets
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water (not boiling).
Remove from water and stir in sour cream, confectioners sugar and salt. Blend in crumbs.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Press nuts in surface.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: garden vegetable burrito
directions: Make Ramen according to the directions on package.
Serve in soup bowl.
Add a slice of cheese; let it melt.
Stir and eat.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream oleo and 1/2 c. powdered sugar.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.
Mold into 1 inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
May be placed close as cookies do not spread.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
After cookies have cooled, roll in 1 cup of powdered sugar.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery and water and salt in Dutch oven; simmer covered about 20 minutse or until tender.
Mash mixture once or twice with potato masher, leaving some vegetable pieces whole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly until soup is thoroughly heated.
Yields about 7 cups.

title: divinity - never fail
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water slowly until it cracks in cold water or 250°.
Add slowly to beaten egg whites, beating constantly until stiff enough to hold imprint of the beaters.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Drain the oysters.
Lay an oyster across 1/2 slice of Bacon. Sprinkle each one with the seasonings and parsley.
Roll entire strip of Bacon around the Oyster and fasten with toothpicks. Place oysters on a rack in shallow baking dish.
Bake in a 450 degree oven for 10 mins, or until bacon is crisp.
Remove toothpicks and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw
broccoli
and
cook rice according to directions. In
a skillet,
melt
margarine
and
add onions;
cook until tender. Add
water,
soup
and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in thawed broccoli and add rice and stir.
Put in a
buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until it bubbles up.

title: jam cake and easy penuche icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add jam and cranberries.
Add rest of ingredients as desired.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Ice cake with Easy Penuche Icing.

title: o' henry bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat. Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the chips in microwave using medium heat.
Mix melted chips and spread on top of cereal mixture.
Cool and cut.
(May cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.)

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs and beat lightly.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and spread mixture in long pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Then put marshmallows over hot cake and return to oven until marshmallows are melted.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: egg bread for dressing
directions: Mix altogether and put in 7 x 2 1/2 x 11 or 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook the chicken in a large pan.
Take meat off bone and chop. Cook chopped onion and pepper in oleo until soft.
Add to the chicken, onion, pepper, peas, Ro-Tel and soups.
Add 1 can of water.
Cook all of this and when it comes to a boil, turn heat down and cook slowly.
Cook noodles in the chicken broth, drain and add to chicken mixture, then add cheese.

title: spam-wich
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve in onion rolls or any bread with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, butter and lemon juice.
Gently fold in shrimp and onion.
Serve on your favorite cracker.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add all other ingredients except noodles.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini sticks
directions: Cut
unpeeled
zucchini
into
strips, dip each zucchini strip into the egg, then in
the crumbs.
Season the strips and place into frying pan with oil.
Cook on each side until golden brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop up carrots and ham, if desired.
Cook for 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice hard-boiled eggs in half.
Scoop yolks out into a small mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise, pickles, salt and pepper; mix well. Fill egg halves with mixture.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop enough apples to make 2 1/3 cups.
Pour sugar over apples; let stand 10 minutes.
Add oil and eggs to apple mixture. Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add dry mixture to apple mixture.
Then fold in 1 cup raisins and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use a 13 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: mocha dessert bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In a small bowl, stir together coffee, extract and water until coffee is dissolved.
Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Combine sour cream, sugars, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Add coffee mixture and beat well. Gradually add dry ingredients and butter; mix until well blended. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake for 65 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean from center.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, milk and vegetables.
Over medium heat, heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans.
Spread mixture on top of whole graham crackers.
Mix jello and let start to thicken before pouring over mixture.
Add whip cream and chill several hours.

title: butter pecan torte
directions: Butter
a 13 x 9 x 2-inch
pan.
Press
graham
cracker crumbs onto the bottom.
Mix pudding with
milk and beat well. Blend in the softened ice cream and pour over crust.
Top with Cool
Whip and sprinkle with crushed
Heath
bars.
Store
in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar with eggs; stir in buttermilk, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: low-fat eggnog
directions: In blender, combine egg substitute, skim milk, vanilla and rum flavorings and sugar substitute.
If desired, add food coloring. Cover and blend on high speed until frothy.
Chill thoroughly. Serve garnished with a sprinkling of nutmeg.
Each 1/2 cup serving has 58 calories, 0.8 g fat and 1.9 mg cholesterol.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 7 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve 1/2 cup drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook mushrooms and onions in drippings over medium-high heat until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and half and half. Stir constantly over medium-high heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sherry.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, mix spaghetti, chicken, bacon and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Pour cream sauce over spaghetti mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage; place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Scramble eggs (soft) and place on top of sausage.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted and browned to taste.
This may be halved for smaller dish.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes, but do not peel.
Cut 3/4-inch slices.
Place on paper towels.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter and rice cereal. Shape into 60 balls. In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip the balls into chocolate mixture, using toothpicks. Leave small amount of peanut butter showing at top. Place on waxed paper until set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: May substitute sugar with Sweet 'N Low.
Preheat oven to 350°. Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Can put in cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar,
milk and margarine for 8 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.

title: spaghetti franciscron
directions: Fry bacon, brown beef and add to bacon; drain fat.
Next, add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add creamed corn and garlic salt.
Pour sauce over spaghetti.
Pour half of cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce and spaghetti over cheese, then add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise. Set aside.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions.
Bring milk, butter and cottage cheese to a boil.
Drain pasta or fettucini; add milk and cheese mixture.
Toss well, then add nutmeg or parsley and ground pepper.
Serve warm with French garlic bread and salad.

title: candy corn popcorn balls
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, microwave butter and marshmallows on high for 1 1/2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed. Stir in gelatin until well mixed. Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn and candy corn in large bowl. Mix lightly until well coated. Shape into 15 balls with greased or moistened hands. Wrap each ball in plastic wrap and tie with raffia or ribbon, if desired.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine.
Rinse in cold water.
Put 1/2 bottle Salad Supreme seasoning into Italian dressing.
Pour over linguine well and chill.

title: torta di risso
directions: Beat eggs; fold in all other ingredients.
Place olive oil on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Pour mixture on top of bread crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown on the bottom.

title: honey butter
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
(Excellent on toast or hot biscuits.)

title: curried shrimp and rice(microwave)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, combine Vita Fiber, honey according to taste and spices.
Mix with a fork or your fingers.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch baking pan; bake 5 to 10 minutes only.
Watch the mixture carefully as it tends to burn quickly.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in square greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix soup, mushrooms, mayonnaise, bell pepper, pimento and onion.
Pour over drained macaroni and mix well.
Grate cheese and stir into macaroni mixture.

title: hamburger taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together and drain.
Add remaining ingredients to hamburger and cook till cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first three ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients, mix well.
Cover. Chill about 2 hours.

title: basic french fries
directions: Trim ends and sides off potatoes and cut into sticks 1/4 inch by about 3 inches.	Fry once in deep fryer at 325° in vegetate oil until tender and just starting to turn color.
Drain and let cool. Fry again at 375° for 1 to 2 minutes until crisp and brown. Drain; toss with salt and serve immediately.

title: charlotte's vegetable bake
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling salted water for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.

Drain. Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart, oiled baking dish. Add zucchini, tomatoes and croutons, tossing until combined. Pour milk into saucepan. Whisk in cornstarch, seasoned salt, black pepper and dill weed. Add butter. Bring to a boil. Cook, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Pour over vegetables. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley. Serves 4.
Serve with poultry and baked potatoes.

title: lime spring salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Mix cheese and pineapple together.
Add all other ingredients to gelatin mixture and congeal.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, mayonnaise, sherry, Tabasco sauce, onion salt, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce; mix until smooth.
Add olives.
Cover and chill until firm.
Shape into a ball.
Roll ball in dried beef and parsley mixture.
(Parsley and beef may be chopped in food processor.)
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: oven crusty fish
directions: Set aside corn flake crumbs. Cut fish into serving pieces, allowing about 1/4 pound for each serving.

Combine milk and salt. Dip fish in milk, then in crumbs. Arrange on well oiled baking sheet or shallow pan. Sprinkle fish with vegetable oil. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salt water for 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water; let cool.
Drain juice of fruit and cook fruit juice with eggs, flour and sugar until thick; then cool.
Mix with macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Add drained fruit, marshmallow and cool whip.
Chill before serving.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown meat; add onions and peppers.
Cook until just tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 hour.

title: super-easy fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Put in greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Pour soup over beans, then spread onion rings on top and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients adding Cool Whip last.
Set in refrigerator until chilled.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Take a sharp knife and make jabs all over the roast on both sides.
Put roast in flat oven dish.
Mix together the ingredients for marinade.
Pour over meat and refrigerate, covered.
Turn every 2 hours.
Cook on grill; turn every 10 minutes.
Baste with marinade.
Allow 30 minutes for rare, 45 minutes for medium and 60 minutes for well done roast.

title: sesame shrimp(serves 2)
directions: In skillet or wok, cook sesame seed in oil until lightly toasted. Add shrimp, onions, 1 tablespoon of soy sauce and the ginger. Stir-fry just until shrimp are heated. Serve over rice with additional soy sauce.

title: fancy cheese and onion biscuits
directions: Put in muffin tin.
Melt margarine and pour over muffins. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: spicy cornmeal cod
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Cut fish into 4 x 2-inch pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients except eggs and margarine.
Dip fish into eggs.
Then coat with cornmeal mixture.
Place fish on ungreased cookie sheet.
Drizzle margarine over fish.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, turning fish once, until golden brown.

title: "tis the season" chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle rice in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread package of seasonings over rice.
Arrange chicken on top.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, butter and sugar; press firmly into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat eggs with fork, mix in remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cooperation cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 4 items together.
Beat well. Mix next 3 ingredients. Add and stir.
Add last 3 ingredients. Stir.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, Karo and salt; cook 5 minutes.
Add soda and pour over popped corn; stir until corn is coated.
Place on cookie sheet and put in 200° oven for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; melt cheese in soup.
Cook broccoli as directed and drain; put in layers in greased casserole.
Crush stuffing and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: quick casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in large casserole.
Lay chicken or pork chops on top of mixture.
Then sprinkle chicken or chops with Lipton dry onion soup.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 hours at 350° to 375°.

title: scalloped tomatoes #2
directions: Saute chopped onion in melted butter in saucepan.
Add sugar, basil, salt, pepper and small bread cubes.
Arrange 1 can of tomatoes in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half of bread mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven (375°) for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hoe cake corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients with hot boiling water. Have iron hoe cake baker greased good and hot. Pour in hot baker. Brown and turn once.

title: bird cage snack
directions: Take one chocolate chip cookie and put drops of peanut butter around the edge.
Stick pretzel sticks in peanut butter and place other cookie on top. Don't forget to put birds in their cages.
Top with candy canes. Good luck!

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside. Blend pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip; set aside. In a large bowl, blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine; add pudding mixture and blend well. In an unused 8-inch flower pot, layer 1/3 Oreos, 1/2 pudding mixture, 1/3 Oreos, 1/2 pudding mixture and 1/3 Oreos.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Cook chicken until well done in plenty of broth.
With your chopped veggies to make your stock, remove chicken and remove skin and bones.
Make a couple of dozen meat balls (or more).
Roll them real small.
While pot is boiling, add acini de pepe and drop in meat balls.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook long enough for pasta and meat balls to be cooked.
Serve, putting one or two meat balls in each bowl.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for one hour or until top springs back.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix together well and refrigerate.
Marinate at least one hour before cooking.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Add all other ingredients to whipped cream cheese.
Bake in small casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika. Serve hot with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar and white syrup for 3 1/2 minutes on Full Power.
Stir.
Cook 3 1/2 minutes on Full Power.
Add butter; stir. Cook 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Add vanilla.
Spread on cookie sheet and let harden.

title: overnight salad
directions: Best if you use a glass bowl.
Clean and tear spinach.
Layer with bacon and egg.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar on egg. Clean and tear lettuce.
Layer on egg.
Layer peas and onion on lettuce.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar on onion.
Mix sour cream and mayo; spread on the onion layer.
Sprinkle with your favorite cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving. Enjoy!

title: crab snacks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Spread on each muffin half; sprinkle with paprika.
Cut each muffin half into quarters. Broil 3 minutes or until light brown.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas; pour into mixing bowl.
Grate eggs and cheese over peas.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well with a fork so the peas won't get mashed.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons salad dressing or mayonnaise, if desired.

title: mrs. felicia's peanut candy
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in electric skillet. Set thermostat to 280°.
Bring mixture to boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off skillet.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla; stir until melted and blended.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cool candy before cutting. Makes 2 pounds.

title: prune cake
directions: Cook prunes until tender.
Mix marshmallows into prunes while hot.
Add	crackers
and
nuts;
place
in
container. Sprinkle crumbs on top of loaf; let cool and slice.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in dish.
Cook in microwave on high for 16 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour slowly over egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue beating until mixture becomes very stiff and loses its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Pour water over Jell-O.
Mix and set to cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour all into a 9 x 12-inch pan, which has onion flakes on bottom.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar well. Mix in all remaining ingredients. Spread mixture in ungreased pie plate or similar pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buffet beef cubes
directions: Shake beef cubes with flour in bag until cubes are well coated. Brown in shortening in 10-inch skillet.
Combine tomato juice with sugar, salt, sweet basil, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar. Add to browned meat; add onion and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 2 hours until meat is tender and liquid cooks down to gravy consistency.
Serve over hot rice.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: hungarian macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain. Combine soup, mayonnaise, mushroom juice and pimiento juice. Toss macaroni with onion, green pepper, mushrooms and pimiento.
Arrange in two layers with cheese in the middle.
Pour sauce over and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a buttered casserole at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: susie's taco salad
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef with taco seasoning; drain meat.
Let meat cool.
Add Doritos.
Mix and toss with other ingredients, except dressing.
Pour dressing over and toss.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt the margarine and cocoa in large saucepan.
Add sugar and eggs.
Next, add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
While hot, cover top of cake with marshmallows.
Put Chocolate Icing on top.

title: 5 cup casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rainbow fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together condensed milk and lemonade, using a mixer on medium speed.
Add remaining ingredients and stir by hand until well coated.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place on warm unit on stove for about 1 1/2 hours.
When ready to serve, add orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve in punch cup with a stick of cinnamon.
Yields 25 servings.

title: barbecue-sauced potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange potato and onion slices in microwave-safe bowl, placing the smaller pieces in the center.
Stir together the water and barbecue sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on 100% power for 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes and onions are tender.
Makes 4 servings, 112 calories per serving.

title: chopped beef
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread mixture on slices of Buddig beef. Roll and freeze.
While frozen, cut into 1/3.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and onions.
Place a layer of potatoes, then a layer of onions.
Continue alternating layers until desired amount is needed.
Lay the pork chops on the top layer.
Spread cream of chicken soup directly from can over top of pork chops.
Cook for 1 hour at 400°.
(Preheat oven.)

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Scrape or peel carrots.
Cook in a small amount of water until tender, but not soft, about 15 minutes.
Remove from water.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Mix honey and orange juice, pour over carrots.
Bake 15 minutes in moderate oven at 350°.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix raisins in bowl.
Cover with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix raisins, pecans, carrots and sugar. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, blend in salad dressing.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Mix well and let stand overnight. Before serving, add 2 bananas, sliced.

title: canolli cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake mix as directed.
Beat heavy cream. Add powdered sugar, vanilla and 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Add Ricotta cheese and chocolate chips.
Tunnel cake; fill in the filling.
Top with whipped cream and cherries.

title: chocolate peanut butter milkshake
directions: Place peanut butter, chocolate syrup and milk in blender and blend.
Add ice cream and blend again.
Pour into glass.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add egg yolk.
Beat well.
Add flour which has been sifted with cinnamon.
With hand, knead dough in bowl until mixture holds together.
Spread dough on ungreased cookie sheet into a 14 x 9-inch rectangle.
(You can roll the dough gently with a floured rolling pin.)
Beat egg white slightly. Brush onto cookie dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes until lightly browned.
As soon as cookie sheet is removed from oven, cut rectangle lengthwise into 3 strips, then cut each strip crosswise into 1 inch wide pieces.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 42 cookies.

title: andy's cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium nonstick skillet, cook and stir beef over medium high heat until browned.
Remove from heat; pour off drippings.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, soup, pepper and seasoning. In greased 4-quart baking dish, combine pasta, sauce mixture and 2 cups of the cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese on top.
Bake for 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: indian bread(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine the milk and molasses.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart steam mold, cover and place on a rack in a deep kettle that has a close fitting lid.
Pour enough boiling water into the kettle to come about halfway up the mold.
Cover the kettle and steam the mold for 3 hours.
Remove the mold from the kettle and let stand 20 minutes.
Remove the cover and let stand 10 minutes longer. Loosen the edges with spatula; invert onto plate.
Let stand until bread unmolds.
Serve with lots of butter.

title: indonesian chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix honey, soy sauce, teriyaki sauce, ginger, water and garlic in small mixing bowl.
Stir until all ingredients are well blended.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and cornflakes.
Turn into shallow buttered casserole dish.
Combine cheese and cornflakes and spread on top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon chiffon
directions: Mix well.
Fold into package #1.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: -                         seafood pizza
directions: Mix together the cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Blend well and spread over a 12 inch platter.
Refrigerate until set, about 2 or 3 hours.
Then spread the cocktail sauce over the first mixture. Spread the drained shrimp on top and sprinkle with parsley.
Chill well.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: glop
directions: Brown beef in skillet with onion. Cook macaroni as directed. When done, add to beef. Add tomato soup. Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple pudding
directions: Peel and slice apples into buttered electric skillet. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and cinnamon.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar with softened butter.
Add and combine remaining ingredients in given order to make cake batter of pouring consistency.
Pour over apples.
Do not stir.
Bake, covered, at 225° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon cream syrup
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and cinnamon.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; cool 5 minutes. Stir in evaporated milk.
Serve warm over crepes, pancakes or waffles.
Makes 1 2/3 cups syrup.

title: easy onion dip
directions: Mix and serve with potato chips or fresh vegetables.

title: crab louis
directions: Check crab meat and remove any cartilage.
On 4 plates, arrange the lettuce leaves.
Place 4 ounces of crab meat in the center of lettuce.
Place 4 slices of tomato and egg around the crab meat. Pour over 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Garnish with the olives.
Serve remaining sauce separately.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Dump remainder of ingredients into the butter.
Do not stir.
Drop the fruit into the mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and pepper sauce in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until boiling.
Stir.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 days to blend flavors.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add orange juice; chill until partly thickened.
Add mandarin oranges (drained) and crushed pineapple (drained).
Chill until set in a 12 x 18-inch dish.

title: holiday cheer punch
directions: Make syrup from the first 5 ingredients and chill.
When ready to serve, combine the last 3 ingredients and the syrup in a punch bowl.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and fold in 5 to 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Add a can of peach slices, if desired.

title: gen's dessert
directions: Layer ice cream sandwiches in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon Kahlua over ice cream; let soak in.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Brown almonds in margarine; they burn easily.
Stir constantly. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: turtle cake(this is very, very rich!)
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package; pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: debbie's apple energy
directions: Put apples in a glass bowl with lemon juice and microwave on High, 4 to 5 minutes, until soft.
Add cinnamon and microwave on High 1 minute more.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine pineapple, carrots, apple and walnuts and add jello. Let marinate overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain or cook bacon until crisp and crumble. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Make this the night before serving and refrigerate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt together; add to egg yolks.
Add milk and cook over boiling water until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool.
Add nut meats and pour into crumb shell.
Spread with meringue; bake as directed.

title: parolini spaghetti
directions: In large crock-pot, add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and finely grated zucchini on high.
Chop onion and bell pepper. Rinse mushrooms, then saut in large skillet with butter, stirring until cooked.
Drain and add to crock-pot.
Add minced garlic, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Now saut meat until cooked, drain and add to crock-pot.
Stir together and turn crock-pot to low and simmer 1 to 4 hours.
Boil water and cook spaghetti noodles for 10 minutes.
Serve sauce over noodles with salad and garlic French bread.

title: jello shots(adults only)
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water and stir until Jell-O is completely dissolved. Add vodka, liqueur and cranberry juice. Stir well. Pour into little plastic cups and leave in refrigerator overnight. When ready to serve, squirt a little whipped cream on top. How to eat a Jell-O shot: Put plastic cup in mouth; close mouth enough to let tongue go around the inside rim to loosen the Jell-O from the cup. Down it in one swallow.

title: ham strata
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Butter or Pam the pan.
Place one layer of bread down.
Arrange half the ham and cheeses.
Repeat another layer of bread and rest of ham and cheeses.
Combine eggs, seasonings and milk.
Beat slightly with a fork.
Pour over the layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked macaroni and cheese with sausage
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Break up the sausage into a frying pan and brown to cook out the fats, being sure to break up the pieces as they cook; drain.
Prepare a medium white sauce by melting the butter in a saucepan.
Add the flour to the butter, blending into a pasty substance.
Add about 1/2 cup of the milk and blend well; add the remaining milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Take off heat source and add the cheeses to the sauce and stir until melted.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in salad oil until light brown.
Add celery and beef.
Cook until beef has lost its red color.
Add tomato puree, catsup, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for at least 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Just before serving, split hamburger rolls and toast.

title: safarancho
directions: Pour oil in bottom of skillet and arrange meat on it. Sprinkle the rice over the meat.
Add remaining ingredients to the boiling water and pour over all.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Allow to stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: easy steak and gravy
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan.
Coat steak with flour.
Brown quickly on both sides.
Drain off oil.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Chop onion over top.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer with lid on for 1 hour.

title: homemade pimiento cheese
directions: Mix eggs, vinegar and sugar together.
Cut cheese into mixture.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts. Take off heat and add chopped pimientos.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together oil and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt. Add buttermilk and lemon flavoring.
Mix well and add egg yolks. Beat egg whites until peaks form and fold these into batter.
Pour into tube pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven during baking.

title: mom's pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg, pumpkin and vanilla and stir, mixing well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add nuts or raisins and stir.
Drop teaspoon size dough onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Bring water to rolling boil.
Add shrimp and continue to simmer for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand in water for several hours.
Refrigerate in some of the caraway water.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Peel and mash into large bowl.
You will need 1 1/2 cups mashed potatoes.

title: shrimp-tomato-cheese pie
directions: Beat mayonnaise, egg and egg yolks together.
Add grated cheeses, shrimp and tomatoes.
In a separate pan, saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add salt and pepper, basil, parsley, chives and garlic.
Add sauteed vegetables to mayonnaise and egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shells. Sprinkle with bread crumbs, melted butter and paprika.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 45 minutes until set.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: cold crabmeat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and 30 large marshmallows (do not boil).
Add vanilla and green food coloring.
Mix well.
Add cornflakes and mix until all cornflakes are green.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Place 1 red cinnamon candy in center of each cookie.
Let stand uncovered to dry.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cover chicken with water; cook until tender.
Strain broth. Pull chicken off bones.
You can chill broth and remove fat at this point.
Cook onions and potatoes in broth until tender.
Add tomatoes and chicken.
Cook, uncovered, 2 hours.
Add corn, butter beans and tomato paste.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Season to taste.
Simmer, covered, on warm heat until desired consistency.
Mash with potato masher.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Fry meat real slow for a few minutes.
Add onions and cook a little longer.
Add all other ingredients and cook or simmer for one hour.
What is left, cool and freeze to be used later.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Melt slowly on low heat marshmallows, butter and vanilla.
Add food coloring after marshmallows are melted.
(Stir in coloring.) Remove from heat.
Stir in corn flakes or Rice Krispies.
Make sure all the corn flakes or Rice Krispies turn green.
Empty contents on a tray which has been covered in wax paper.
Mold mixture into a circle shape with your hands.
If desired, you can add maraschino cherries or small silver ball cake decorations. Refrigerate until firm.
Good for Christmas.

title: creamed soup
directions: Cook all ingredients for
minutes.	Puree
all then add 1 cup milk.
Preheat and serve.
You may use canned milk.

title: overnight cauliflower salad
directions: Using large plastic bowl with cover or large glass bowl, put ingredients in layers as they are listed.
Seal tightly.
(You can stretch Saran Wrap tightly over bowl.) Put in refrigerator overnight.
Toss just before serving.
If you want to use part of this salad, dip straight down and put in another bowl to mix.
Be sure to allow at least 12 hours for the topping to get crunchy. Do not skimp on or substitute bacon.

title: beef cherry-yaki
directions: Combine sherry, soy sauce, lemon juice and ginger root.
Slice meat (thinly) and marinate with cherries in sherry mixture overnight.

title: inexpensive layer cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Add vanilla to milk; add alternating with sifted dry ingredients to shortening mixture (sift flour, baking powder and salt).
Pour batter in greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave pecan crisp squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and fibrous membranes.
Place cut side down in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one corner to vent.
Microwave at High 6 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.
While squash is cooking, toss together crumbs, pecans, butter, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
After squash has cooked 6 minutes, turn cut side up and divide filling among the 4 halves.
Re-cover with plastic wrap and microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes, until squash is tender.
Remove plastic wrap and let stand 5 minutes until serving.

title: nanime bars (cookies)
directions: Layer 1:
Put 1/2 cup butter, granulated sugar, unsweetened chocolate and vanilla in top of double boiler and cook over boiling water until well blended.
Add egg and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring.
Add crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Mix with slotted spoon.
Press into 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture. Stir in oats.
Add raisins and pecans as desired.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° until browned.

title: sprouts in an eggshell(activity for kids)
directions: Set empty eggshell in egg cup or napkin ring.
Draw a face on the eggshell.
Place 3 damp cotton balls inside each eggshell. Sprinkle 1/8 teaspoon of alfalfa seeds over cotton balls inside eggshell and keep cotton damp.
In two or three days the seeds will begin to sprout.
Put in a sunny spot.
As the sprouts grow, your child can give the egg friend a "haircut."
Sprinkle the clippings on a salad or put in a sandwich.
Fun to make 1 for each family member.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large iron skillet, combine oil, rice and onion.
Saute. Add tomatoes, water, chicken broth and cumin.
Steam on low heat 15 minutes.
Can add chopped jalapenos for hot rice.

title: biscotti
directions: Mix the baking powder, soda, pinch of salt and flour.
Add the eggs and beat 3 minutes.
Add the sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in 3 Pyrex greased Reynolds Wrap lined loaf pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Cut slices into 3 pieces.
Re-bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Store 2 to 3 days at room temperature, tightly closed. Serve.
Keeps indefinitely.
Makes 62.

title: finger paint
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat with eggbeater until thick. This can be used on shiny surfaced paper (freezer wrap works well) or washable surface.

title: almond cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Combine beaten egg, milk and almond extract.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 16 to 18 minutes.
May place one almond half on each cookie before baking.
Makes 48.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Pour lemon juice over crabmeat.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to crabmeat and lemon juice.
Put in saucepan and heat at low temperature.
Place in a serving bowl and serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into a ball and chill.

title: oven stew
directions: Add cut up carrots, celery and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake 6 hours at 250°.

title: spinach meat loaf
directions: Mix egg, tomato paste, crumbs, Italian seasoning, garlic and onion powder.
Stir in spinach which has been squeezed and dry. Add meat mix well.
Bake for 40 minutes, top with catsup and Parmesan cheese, bake 5 - 10 minutes more or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dishes).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter; mix together and press into pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: pineapple salad(weight watchers)
directions: Heat pineapple in its own juice.
Add jello mix; let cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Boil for 7 1/2 minutes.
Pour over chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and salt in a large bowl.
Beat well and add 1 1/2 to 3 cups broken nut meats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Enjoy!

title: fig cookies
directions: Mix the 7 ingredients in order listed first.
Mix and sift the flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon and add to the first mixture. Add the pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: seaside salad
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner according to directions on the box. Set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, mix together chopped eggs, peas, pimento, tuna and relish.
Add macaroni mix.
Then add salt, pepper and salad dressing.
Mix well and chill at least 2 hours. Serves 8 (2/3 cup) per lettuce cup.
Celery and onions may be added, if desired.

title: all-bran extra fiber muffins
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the All-Bran and the milk; let stand until cereal softens.
Blend in the egg and vegetable oil; beat well.
Add the flour mixture, stirring only to combine the ingredients.
Pour batter into a muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: In top of double boiler put brown sugar and butter.
Break and scatter over this the white bread.
Sprinkle over this the cinnamon, nutmeg and raisins.

title: carnations famous fudge(makes 2 pounds)
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
In saucepan, combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Hint: For thicker fudge, use a 7 x 5-inch loaf pan.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix and bake all ingredients except berries until thick and clear.
Place strawberries into baked and cooled pie shell.
After boiled mixture has cooled, pour over berries.
Place in refrigerator.
Add Cool Whip when ready to serve.
Makes 1 pie.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Add onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and as many cucumbers it takes to fill the bowl. Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep for approximately one week or more.

title: harvest stew
directions: Brown stew beef in fat.
Add salt, pepper, chopped onion, tomatoes, water and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots and macaroni.
Simmer 30 minutes, then add corn and any cooked vegetables you desire.
Do not drain vegetables; juices are used in broth.

title: duggins beef roast
directions: Spread mustard over top and sides of roast.
Sprinkle with thyme leaves.
Place roast on rack in baking pan.
Cover tightly with bacon slices, wrapping them around meat.
Bake meat at 325° until a meat thermometer registers 160°.
Cook for 1 3/4 hours. Check for doneness with a fork.
Add onions 40 minutes before roast is expected to be ready.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes or tomato wedges.

title: kringla
directions: Mix water, yeast and 2 cups flour and let raise about 1/2 hour.
Place in bowl and mix 6 cups flour, shortening, salt, sugar and cream.
Add yeast mixture and knead well.
Let raise 1/2 hour. Roll in 1/2-inch diameter strings and shape into figure eights. Glaze top with beaten egg and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to temperature on back of biscuit package.
In a cake pan, pour half of the gravy in the bottom of pan.
Put half of chicken on top of gravy.
Place biscuits on top of gravy and chicken mixture.
Place rest of chicken on top of biscuits and cover with remaining gravy.
Place pan in oven.
Bake for 20 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: In a casserole dish, combine noodles, tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
In a pot, melt cheese and butter. Pour over casserole mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: buddy's lemon pie
directions: Make pie crust by crumbling vanilla wafers in the bottom of pie dish.
Stand wafers up around the edge and mix pie. Separate eggs.
Put yolks in large mixing bowl and beat well.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in pie crust.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Combine first three ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool.
Stir in peanut butter

title: bread pudding
directions: Break up bread in a large bowl.
Add milk and water.
When bread is soft, add flavoring, seasonings, egg and 1/2 an apple. Mix thoroughly and add sugar to taste.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and peanut butter in a pot and cook over medium heat, stirring continuously, until peanut butter and sugar are melted.
Remove from heat and add cereal.
Mix well and quickly pour in a 9x13 pan and spread with a spatula.
Rub margarine on spatula to make spreading easier.

title: scalloped turkey
directions: Clean celery and cut up into small pieces, using the celery leaves also.
Chop onion.
Put butter to melt on stove; add onion and celery.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Break bread in large container.
Bake turkey with water on it for broth.
Boil eggs and cut up.
Whe turkey is done, cut up.
Add turkey, eggs (both boiled and raw) and celery and onion mixture to bread.
Put broth on to boil and add chicken base and more water to it.
Pour hot broth over bread mixture.
Stir and put into 2 long cake pans. Bake about 45 minutes or until brown and boiling.
Bake at 350°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: maggie's pasta and shrimp salad
directions: Drain artichokes; save liquid; quarter.
Slice cherry tomatoes in half.
Peel, cook and chill shrimp.
Slice black olives into rings.
Drain liquid from chickpeas.
Mince garlic.
Dice scallions.
Dice green pepper.
Toss all ingredients with liquid from artichokes, torn basil, lemon juice, salt, oregano (all to taste).
Add extra olive oil if needed.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and milk; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook until a soft ball forms when dropped in cold water or stir a little in a small amount of peanut butter until it becomes hard.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add pecans, if desired.
Mix well and pour on wax paper (use a cut open paper bag under the wax paper).
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: kolachy
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large, warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, beaten eggs and half of the flour; beat until smooth. Stir in remaining flour to make a slightly stiff dough.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill overnight. Spread mixture over all of tortillas to edges real well. Roll up and pin with toothpick. Chill overnight. Cut into 3/4 inch rolls.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put cider in percolator.
In percolator basket, put brown sugar, cinnamon stick, cloves and salt; perk.

title: neiman-marcus toll house cookies
directions: Cream butter
and
both
sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Mix all dry ingredients.
(Blend oatmeal in blender,
1 cup
at a time.
The 5 cup measurement is taken before it's blended.) Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, a little at
a time.
Stir
well
after
each addition.
Add chocolate chips, grated
Hershey
bar
and
chopped
nuts.
Drop
scant teaspoon of batter 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake
at 375° approximately 6 minutes.
Makes more than anyone should have in the house.

title: vegetable chili medily(serves 12 people)
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving in heavy 10-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook ground beef and onions until meat loses its pink color; stir often.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, butter, eggs, oil and vanilla. Add small amounts of flour to mixture. Drop by spoon on ungreased baking sheet. Press out flat. Bake 15 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: pioneer pumpkin pie
directions: Combine in order listed; mix well and pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake in quick oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for remaining time, about 45 minutes, or until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: dirt cake
directions: Chop package of Oreo cookies in blender or mash until real fine, like sand.
Set aside.
Fix pudding according to directions. Blend cream cheese, butter, confectioners sugar and prepared pudding.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; cream again.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture; blend.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
This is a stiff dough.
Mold into long squares or rectangles, or press into foil boxes or juice cans, to shape.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Slice thin. Place 1/2 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet quickly.
Cool on a rack. Empty foil boxes or cans are good "shapers" and all cookies will be the same size.
These cookies will keep indefinitely, if you hide them!

title: brownie muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder, cinnamon and 3/4 tsp salt; make a well in center. combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just till moistened (batter should be lumpy). Fold in chopped nuts. Fill greased or paper bake cup lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add dry ingredients; mix well and add nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 or 2 minutes until chips are soft.
Remove from oven.
Run knife through batter to marbelize.
Continue baking 12 minutes longer.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix shortening and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Beat in 1 cup of flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well; add the rest of the flour.
Mix well.
Shape dough into little 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Take a glass and grease bottom, then dip into sugar.
Press down onto the dough balls to flatten.
Bake 15 minutes until lightly brown.

title: autumn gold salad
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Cool slightly and add sour cream, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Beat until smooth; chill until partly set.
Fold in cheese, apples and celery.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into a 6 to 6 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce; trim with lemon-brushed apple slices, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage scotch eggs
directions: Dry eggs well, then roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Mold tightly the sausage on the eggs.
Roll in beaten eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Deep fry in oil until sausage is cooked through.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 big pans.
May be halved.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oil and oleo with sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and milk.
Add all dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla cheese dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use as a dip for fresh fruits: apples, pears, bananas, grapes, strawberries, blueberries, pineapple or kiwi.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and simmer 30 minutes.
Can be put into pint jars after simmering.
Seal and put in water bath for 15 minutes. Makes about 6 pints.

title: curried orange chicken
directions: Cut up chicken. Sprinkle chicken pieces with curry powder. Rub into meat. Arrange in baking dish, skin side down.
Combine orange, juice, honey and mustard in small saucepan.
Simmer until blended.
Pour over chicken.
