Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and continue baking 20 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Keep warm.

title: english toffee
directions: You will also need a candy thermometer and a large 12 x 18-inch pan.

title: squash custard pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until set in middle).
Crust bakes better if you bake for a few minutes before filling.

title: oven pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops in hot fat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine other ingredients and pour evenly over pork chops.
Cover and bake in slow oven for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add additional water if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place apples in bottom of a greased
inch round baking dish. Sprinkle with a mixture of the sugar and cinnamon. Mix dry ingredients together.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Butter sides of a pan.
In a large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, baking soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk and corn syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Cook and stir to soft ball stage or 234°.
Remove from heat; add butter and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to drop on a buttered cookie sheet.
If it begins to get too thick, add 1 teaspoon hot water. Makes about 45 pralines.
They taste like the famous pralines of New Orleans.

title: red apple inn rolls(from heber springs)
directions: Pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Mix yeast with warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Make a well in flour. Add eggs, yeast and other mixture.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Flour a board with enough flour to knead.
Roll out. Cut with cookie cutter and brush both sides with butter, then fold over; let rise.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: bread pudding(layered in double boiler.)
directions: Sprinkle bread with brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Mix milk, eggs and vanilla; pour over bread.
"Do not stir."
Cook 2 to 3 hours (medium heat) in double boiler.
Keep water boiling.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef and chopped onions together.
Form into 1-inch meatballs and brown in frying pan.
Place meatballs in casserole dish and pour soup over top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: best ever chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in saucepan and set aside.
Combine egg yolks and milk and stir into sugar mixture. Add margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Spoon into pie shell.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice and onion in margarine.
Place in a greased casserole dish; add mushrooms (drained) and soup plus enough water to make 2 cups.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato mallow
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Heat oven to 350°. In a small mixer bowl, combine sweet potatoes, yogurt, cornstarch, salt and mace. Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Pour sweet mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt together; blend in boiling water and lemonade.
Beat egg yolks and blend into cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and pour into a cooled pie shell. Cool; cover with meringue and brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large stock pot combine chicken stock, potatoes, onion and celery.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in large chunks and place in a bowl.
Cover with oil and onion soup mix.
Mix until potatoes are covered well. Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and dry ingredients, then flavoring and coconut.
Start in cold oven. Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Combine the margarine, brown sugar, hot water and eggs.
Add flour gradually, beating in well.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Add nuts. Pour into a greased 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Cook ripe peaches 10 minutes with 1/2 of the sugar.
Add cherries, rind and orange juice, and remainder of sugar.
Cook 20 minutes.
Seal.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Break into bite-size pieces and place in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Drain Veg All and sprinkle over chicken.
Mix soup, and broth and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, butter and milk and spoon over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Stir and let stand for 20 minutes.
Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish in 350° oven.
Sift together the flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and stir briskly (lumps will remain).
Pour into the baking dish of melted butter; top with peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is browned and it begins to caramelize at edges.

title: oriental catfish
directions: Make a marinade by mixing soy sauce, ginger, red pepper flakes and wine together. Marinate catfish for about 1 hour in the refrigerator. Broil the catfish for approximately 5 to 7 minutes until the flesh starts to flake easily. Baste often with marinade.

title: chicken with rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish, place rice and sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Then combine soup, water and mushrooms; pour 1/2 over rice.
Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in single layer on rice.
Pour remaining one half soup mixture over chicken.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Just before serving fluff rice gently with fork.

title: krispy sweets
directions: Pack whole small or medium cucumbers into a gallon jar with lid.
Add salt, alum and spices.
Add 4 cups cold vinegar and as much water as needed to fill jar.
Seal jar and let stand for 8 weeks.
Drain and wash jar (not pickles).
Cut cucumbers into thick slices and put back in a jar.
Add 6 cups sugar (no liquid).
Shake and roll jar several times a day until sugar becomes syrup.
Will keep months in fridge.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar; add all other ingredients and freeze to slush.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: baked beans and hamburger
directions: Brown meat and drain; drain water off kidney beans and rinse. Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low all night or put on in morning to be done by supper.
Good with barbecue.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, vanilla and salt.
Stir in flour and oats.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Lightly dust with powdered sugar.

title: frankfurters
directions: Place frankfurters on grid over medium coals, turning occasionally.
Broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve grilled frankfurters on buns.
Prepare topping and use as desired.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In a large mixing bowl, beat sugar and shortening.
Add egg and pineapple with juice; beat well. Stir dry ingredients into beaten mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour. Drop with spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in 2-quart pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Add rest of ingredients
and cook for 30 minutes at 400°.
Add one cup of crumbs and brown.

title: rice and peas
directions: Thoroughly cook beans plus 4 tablespoons olive oil, 1/2 ounce margarine, garlic, onion, cayenne pepper, salt, thyme and scallion in 6 cups water.
This will take approximately 2 hours to cook. If water gets low, add a little more.

title: ruby wolfe soup
directions: Boil potatoes.
Drain.
Put all ingredients in a big stew pot with 1 quart of water.
Slow cook about 2 to 3 hours.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450°
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix butter and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Cut the spaghetti squash in half.
Cover with water and simmer until squash is tender and shreds easily into strands.
Drain. Put into a saucepan and add the spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste as needed.

title: maurice salad
directions: Put lettuce in a salad bowl and then add ham, turkey or chicken and the cheese.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over the salad.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: scampi vittorios
directions: Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.
Add shrimp, garlic and parsley; saute until shrimp turns pink, about 2 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Season with pepper.
Stir in lemon juice and wine. Simmer about 2 more minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except tomatoes, in a large bowl. Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Let set in a covered container overnight.
Add tomatoes before serving.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt butter in oblong casserole dish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Layer the next 5 ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Stir and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jalapeno cheese cornbread(texas governor ann w. richards)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients for a wonderful salad.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.

title: good easy chicken dish
directions: Cover with foil. Cook at 275° for 2 1/2 hours. Add a few slivered almonds or mushrooms that have been cooked in butter.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water and sugar. Heat buttermilk slowly to lukewarm. In large bowl, sieve together dry ingredients. Cut in shortening as for biscuits. Add yeast mixture to buttermilk. Mix liquids with dry ingredients as for biscuits, to a soft dough. Put into a large greased bowl; cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: pat's irish cream
directions: Mix coffee with 2 tablespoons cream.
Then in a plastic or glass pitcher (not metal), and with a wooden spoon, add the ingredients in order given.
Store in refrigerator, preferably in a dark bottle.

title: pierogi
directions: Beat eggs, salt, oil and water together.
Add flour and knead until dough is smooth.
(Do not overmix.)
Take a piece of dough and roll out to about 1/8-inch thickness, then cut into 4-inch circles.
Put one tablespoon of desired filling (see below) on half of the circle, then dab the edges of the circle with milk; fold the other half over, pinching the halves together.
Drop into boiling water and cook until the pierogi rises to the top.
When ready to serve, brown pierogi and chopped onions in butter or margarine; serve with sour cream.
Pierogi dough may be made in advance, then oiled slightly, wrapped and kept in the refrigerator for several days.
When pinching the halves together, be sure that it is sealed properly or filling will come out.
Makes about 120.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, Karo and salt to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda, stirring until all is foaming.
Pour over popcorn and stir until covered.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Stir in bananas and water.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir until moist.
Add nuts. Bake 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes and then remove from pan.
Serves 12.

title: nutty buddy pies(makes 3 pies)
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 3 graham cracker crusts.
Top with Hershey's chocolate syrup and chopped peanuts.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 30 to 60 minutes before serving.

title: granola candy
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk and honey; mix well.
Shape mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time, into balls.
Roll in granola cereal, pressing firmly for granola to stick.
Repeat until all peanut butter mixture is used.
Arrange on a tray, cover and refrigerate.
Yields 3 dozen delicious treats.

title: matzo pancakes *
directions: Soak broken up matzo in hot water; drain.
Beat egg yolks well; add matzo.
Continue beating.
Add matzo meal; fold in beaten egg whites.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Drop large spoonfuls of batter into oil.
Fry until brown on one side.
Turn; fry until brown on other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with applesauce or sprinkled with sugar.

title: stuffed pork chop for one person
directions: Cut pocket in pork chop.
Add broth or water to dressing mix. Cook in microwave oven less than 1 minute.
Add grated apple and stuff pork chop.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.
Can be cooked in an electric skillet on medium heat.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring butter or margarine, syrup and sugar to soft boil, about 5 minutes.
Add coloring and pour over salted popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Form into popcorn balls.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Beat eggs with milk and add bread and salt.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish (or pan) cover with fill and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Beat all ingredients with a fork for 1 minute and pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook
potatoes	in
salted
water
until
tender
only. Drain. Heat cream of chicken soup and margarine.	Remove from heat and add
grated
cheese,
sour	cream and onions.
Mix in potatoes and pour in greased dish and bake 20 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Cook ingredients all together for 2 to 3 hours.
Put up in heated canning jars.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients with fork until smooth.
Add 1 heaping tablespoon dried minced onion and dash of cayenne pepper.
Spread over slices of ham to very edge.
Roll, refrigerate overnight and slice.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook onion in oil and butter in pot over medium heat, stirring frequently, 30 minutes until softened and caramelized.
Stir in flour to coat onions; cook 1 minute.
Slowly stir in broth. Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Add sherry.
Spoon soup into 6 individual ovenproof bowls.
Top each with bread and cheese.
Broil briefly to melt cheese.
Serve.

title: sausage 'n egg casserole
directions: Cover bottom of a greased 10 x 6-inch or 7 x 11-inch baking dish with half of grated cheese.
Mix all seasonings with sour cream and pour half over the cheese.
Add crumbled, cooked sausage.
Beat eggs and pour over mixture.
Spoon rest of sour cream mixture over eggs and rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: oven beef tips
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Don't open door until 4 hours are up.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
Good over rice or noodles.

title: stuffed mushroom appetizers
directions: Clean and cut stems from mushrooms, leaving hollow centers. Fill each mushroom center with Mozzarella cheese.
After filling mushrooms, place in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle Italian dressing over all mushrooms.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve warm

title: blender custard pie(makes its own crust.)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture in a greased pie pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy peanut butter bars
directions: Cut together sugar and 1 cup peanut butter.
Crush graham crackers and combine with sugar mixture.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Melt 1/3 cup peanut butter and baking chips.
Pour over top of bars and refrigerate. When set, cut into squares.

title: hot applesauce salad
directions: Combine boiling water with cinnamon candies in a saucepan; stir over low heat to dissolve candies.
Remove from heat, stir in jello and blend in applesauce.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Leave remaining gelatin at room temperature.
Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise; add nuts.
Spread mixture over chilled mixture.
Pour remaining gelatin over cheese.
Chill several hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Serves 9 to 12.
Good with ham, pork, roast or poultry.

title: long island potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until al dente, slice thin and put in large container.
In small bowl mix sugar, mustard, egg, water, salt, pepper, parsley and chopped onion.
Combine the liquid with the sliced potatoes and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain potatoes in strainer, place in bowl and add mayo.
Mix.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until brown.
Serve sliced with your favorite cheese.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Add sugar and let set until dissolved.
Add apples, marshmallows and pecans.
Stir all together.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill.
When ready to serve, stir in whipped cream.
Serves approximately 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pineapple and its juice.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Cut margarine into pats and layer over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good topped with ice cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Place eggs, oil, zucchini and sugar in large mixing bowl. Beat 2 or 3 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the egg mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 loaf pans, well greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of a large double boiler.
Beat at a low speed of an electric mixer for 30 seconds or just until blended.

title: red candy apples
directions: Combine all ingredients, except food coloring and apples. Cook until mixture spins a thread or until the candy stays on the apple.
Add food coloring.
Put a stick into apple and dip into mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pudding mix with crushed pineapple.
Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well, then refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mother's pepper relish
directions: Grind
the
peppers
and
place in a large mixing bowl. Pour enough boiling water over the peppers to cover;
let set 10 minutes.
Drain; add onions and celery seed if using.
Set aside. In	large
saucepan,
boil	vinegar,
salt	and
sugar together. While
boiling
add
pepper-onion mixture.	Boil up well.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze for 1 hour.
When ready to cook cut into small pieces.	Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in generous amount of water until tender; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter.
Mix flour and salt.
Add warm chicken broth to make a firm dough.
Divide into 2 parts and roll thin on floured board.
Have at least 2 quarts of broth in large pot with cooked chicken and bring to a full boil.
Cut dough into strips and drop into boiling broth, one piece at a time.
Cook uncovered at least 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and cook 20 minutes more, covered.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix 1 can sauce and refried beans with meat. Place a scoop of meat and cheese on tortilla; roll up and place in pan. Pour the other can of enchilada sauce over tortillas and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, salt and shortening.
Add boiling water and stir until shortening melts.
Add beaten eggs. Stir.
Add 3 cups of flour and mix well.
In 1 cup of warm water, dissolve the yeast.
Add to first mixture, then add 3 more cups of flour.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Place rolls in greased pan and let rise 2 to 3 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, green pepper and garlic together for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Cook noodles as usual; drain.
Add to meat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, corn, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all together and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
Put cheese on top.
Cook until melted.

title: strawberry yogurt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Beat cake mix (dry), water, oil, egg whites and 1 container yogurt in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds .
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center; cool completely.
Fold remaining container yogurt and 1 or 2 drops red food coloring into whipped topping.
Spread over top of cake. Garnish with strawberries if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: "sunshine"
directions: Take strawberries, sugar and pineapple.
Hull the berries; wash and drain them.
Peel the pineapple and put it through a food grinder.
Put the fruit into a saucepan and bring it slowly to a boil.
Add the sugar and cook until it is thick.

title: rolled butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in egg, cream, baking powder, salt, vanilla, butter extract (if needed) and baking soda.
Gradually add flour.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick. Cut out.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Brown veal patties as directed. Place cooked noodles in bottom of a
long casserole dish. Layer veal patties on top of noodles. Sprinkle
well
with
Parmesan
cheese.
Pour
can of spaghetti sauce over patties.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over spaghetti sauce.
Top
with Parmesan cheese.	Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: kayvon's ninja turtles
directions: Butter two cookie sheets.
Place four pecan halves about 2-inches apart on the sheets.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Set aside.
Drain very well any fruit to be used.
When fruit is dry, add to Jell-O mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving. Serves 6.

title: hamburger casserole seasoning mix
directions: Mix together and store in a resealable bag or container. Makes 5 1/2 cup servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla, carrots and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg-dying kit
directions: Mix 1 cup water, 1/4 cup white vinegar and a few drops food coloring for a homemade version.
Make as many colors as you like.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Brown 1 pound of hamburger meat with one small chopped onion. Add 1/2 to 3/4 tablespoon of chili powder and Tabasco sauce, depending on how much seasoning you want.
Add about 1/2 tablespoon of salt and season to taste.
Stir and simmer all the mixture for about 10 minutes, then add tomato soup and mushroom soup and stir well.
Let cook over low heat for about 20 minutes. Stir often to keep from sticking.
Serve with cooked spaghetti.

title: mushroom-chicken dijon
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in oil about 10 minutes, until brown on both sides.
Remove chicken.
Add a touch more oil, if necessary.
Cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender (if using canned mushrooms, cook them less than broccoli).
Stir in soup, milk, mustard and spices.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer about 10 more minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve contents of skillet over precooked noodles.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: pear honey
directions: Wash, pare and core pears; slice before measuring.
Chop fine. Combine pears and pineapple.
Add rind and juice.
Add sugar and cook over slow heat, stirring frequently.
Cook 20 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars to within 1/4-inch of top.
Put on cap and screw band firmly.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Makes 8 half-pints.

title: shrimp plate
directions: Mix cream cheese with enough milk to make spreading consistency.
Spread on bottom of 10-inch serving plate.
Spread top with desired hotness of Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce. Sprinkle lightly the garlic salt over sauce.
Pour shrimp cocktail sauce over mixture.
Spread thawed shrimp on top.
Refrigerate and serve with favorite crackers.
Enjoy!

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 3 more cups of water, sugar and pineapple juice.
Pour mixture into gallon container and freeze.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash, destem and dry mushroom caps.
Brown sausage and crumble.
Add crumbs and cheese and stir until cheese is melted. Fill caps with sausage.
Melt margarine in bottom of large casserole dish.
Place stuffed caps into margarine.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: yeast dumplings
directions: Thoroughly mix the flour and the yeast in a bowl.
Put in all other ingredients.
Knead everything together until you have a dough.
Let dough rise on warm place until it doubles the size. Knead again.
Form into a roll and cut into 8 pieces.
Flour your hands and form dumplings.
Put them on a floured cookie sheet.
Let them rise until they are doubled.
Put a dish towel over a wide pot with boiling water and fasten to pot handles.
Sprinkle with flour. Put dumplings on top and cover with a bowl.
Cook approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Serve with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in ball or log after first chilling in fridge.
Roll in chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons of parsley, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: *Or use self-rising flour.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Chill milk until ice cold.
Mix 2 eggs, 6 tablespoons sugar, lemon rind and 2 tablespoons lemon juice in a large bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in 4 tablespoons sugar.
Fold in egg yolk mixture.
Whip chilled milk until fluffy.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice and whip until stiff.
Fold into egg mixture.
Pour into tray.
Sprinkle graham crumbs over top.
Freeze.
Do not stir.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Use Bundt pan, pour in about 1/3 of cake batter.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over batter (about 1/2 of Jell-O), then pour another 1/3 of batter and sprinkle rest of Jell-O.
Pour rest of batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: church windows(candy)
directions: Melt at low heat oleo and chocolate chips; cool.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and marshmallows.
Spread 2 cups of coconut on sheets of wax paper.
Mix marshmallows and nuts with melted chocolate. Form into logs and place on paper spread with coconut.
Roll until coconut all sticks to logs.
Wrap in wax paper and freeze overnight.
Slice in pieces while still frozen.

title: no-fat creamy broccoli soup
directions: Combine chopped vegetables (include the peeled and chopped broccoli stems), broth, water and salt in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender. Process the soup in blender (in batches) until pureed.
Return to heat. Add skim milk mixed with cornstarch. Cook 5 to 10 minutes to thicken. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: parmesan chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper in a pot.
Add boiling water and simmer until tender.
Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and milk. Stir into the cooked vegetables. Add Parmesan cheese and simmer a little longer.

title: jumbo chocolate snappers
directions: Place chocolate morsels in top of double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
Cream shortening; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add chocolate, egg and corn syrup, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture, beating just until blended.
Shape dough into balls, using about 3 tablespoons of dough for each ball and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets about 2 1/2 inches apart; bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks and cool completely.
Yield:
About 14 jumbo cookies.

title: sugar-free blueberry muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar replacement, milk and margarine in mixing bowl.
Stir to mix; will be lumpy.
Add berries and nuts. Put in 6 muffin tins coated with vegetable spray.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: stuffed shells with chicken
directions: Boil chicken for 1/2 hour. Place cut up cooked chicken in pan with scallions. Season with spices. Saute. Add spaghetti sauce until mixture is sticky. Cook on warm. Cook box of shells al dente; cool shells. Add 8 ounces sour cream to chicken mixture. Stuff shells. Place in baking dish. Add the rest of spaghetti sauce over shells. Add bag of cheese on top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: claudine's butter icing
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and
milk	in small saucepan.
Cook until thick, (stirring).	Cool. Cream the sugar, butter, Crisco and vanilla.
Beat.
Add cooked and
cooled
mix and beat until it looks like whipped cream, thickened.
Makes
enough to ice a large layer cake.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute
sausages
in greased Dutch oven over medium heat until well
browned.
Transfer
to
plate.
Discard drippings from pot. Add
margarine; heat.
Add onion. Cook over medium-low heat
2 minutes.
Add
garlic. Cook 3 minutes.
Add green and
red pepper,
tomatoes
(drained),
thyme,
chili powder, ground red pepper and sugar. Cook, covered, over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: indian relish
directions: Drain tomatoes and salt overnight.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in jars and seal.

title: chicken crunch
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend broth with soup.
Mix in remaining ingredients except almonds.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sunny autumn cider(sugar-free)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Heat until boiling, then turn down and let simmer until mixture is blended. Remove spices.
Serve warm.

title: butter almond crunch
directions: Spread 1 cup of the mini chocolate chips in a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Spread almonds in shallow pan; toast at 350° for about 7 minutes, or until golden brown.
Set aside.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Put blueberries in 8 x 8-inch pan. Mix flour, baking powder, shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and milk.
Spread over berries. Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour the boiling water over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries, pecans and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into pan.
Put in refrigerator. When Jell-O begins to set, spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining Jell-O over sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and cook on a griddle.
When potatoes are cooked through, but not crispy, pour batter over them.
Cook on both sides.
Serve with sour cream.

title: pineapple frost
directions: Mix salt, ginger and cinnamon in punch bowl.
Combine with softened ice cream.
Stir in milk, then slowly stir in pineapple juice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased baking dish.
Add topping.

title: chocolate turtle cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine and press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: jello cake
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Poke fork holes in cake.
Stir together the powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over cake while warm.

title: kim's chilli
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion; drain off grease. Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk; cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; gradually stir about 1 cup of hot mixture into beaten eggs. Return all to saucepan and cook and stir over medium heat until nearly boiling.
Reduce heat and stir 2 minutes more (do not boil).
Remove from heat; stir in 1 cup coconut, butter and vanilla.

title: canning apples for pie
directions: Make a thin syrup with the sugar and water.
Put quartered apples into weak brine (1 tablespoon salt to each quart of water) until ready.
Drain and drop into boiling syrup.
Cook until transparent (3 to 5 minutes).
Pack into clean, hot glass jars; fill to overflowing with hot syrup.
Seal at once.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone.
Make dip from Velveeta and Ro-Tel.
(Mix together and put in microwave until cheese is melted.)
To dip, add both cans of soup and stir well.
Pour over the boned chicken in casserole dish and add taco Doritos.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Cover bottom of pot in bacon grease.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper and saute until tender.
Add tomato sauce, chopped tomatoes and 2 cans of water. Salt and pepper to taste. Add 4 tbsp. of sugar. Bring to a boil. Add rice and bring to a boil again.
Turn heat down and simmer until rice is tender, but not dry, stirring occasionally. There should be a little juice in the pot.

title: caramel-chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans in unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and drizzle with caramel topping.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs, beating on low speed just until combined. Pour over mixture in crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center appears set.
Cool and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Sift cocoa powder lightly on top.

title: my brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In heavy saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee and cocoa.
Heat to boiling. Pour boiling mixture over the flour mixture in bowl.
Add the sour cream, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into well buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While brownies are baking, prepare frosting.

title: vegetable pizza(appetizer)
directions: Serve cold and cut in small squares.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Mix beans and tuna on medium in a skillet.
Cook until hot. Serve on crackers.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: In a bowl, mix honey, mustard and curry.
Place chicken pieces in 2 Pyrex oblong baking dishes.
Pour sauce over pieces.
Turn pieces over a few times to coat with sauce.
Sprinkle with seasonings to taste.
Add paprika and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
If chicken starts to brown too much, turn oven down slightly and bake a little longer.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: pork chops supper
directions: Place water and barbecue sauce in slow cooker.
Add onion and pepper to sauce.
Place pork chops in sauce.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: deep-dish apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Mix cornstarch, brown sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon together. Coat apples with mixture.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a separate container, mix the vinegar, oil and sugar.
Stir thoroughly and pour over other ingredients, but do not stir. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Stir in the morning.
Keeps as long as you like.
Very good.

title: one egg cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and shortening.
Blend well.
Add alternately dry ingredients and wet ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Use 9-inch round pan or 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: butter crumble
directions: Mix well with hands and bake in a 13 x 8 x 1/2-inch pan, or one 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
When done, stir with a spoon until grainy and store in a closed jar in refrigerator until wanted for use.

title: betty's chocolate balls
directions: In double boiler, melt.
Dip balls with tongs.
Place on wax paper or foil.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt oleo in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with the next 5 items.
Pour milk over top. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray. Combine all ingredients into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut your beef in chunks.
Put in large pot of 8 or more cups of water; cook until beef gets tender.
You can also add your carrots
and onions same time you start your beef.	When your beef
gets	half
done,
put your mixed vegetables, lima beans, soup
greens
and 1 can tomatoes.
When your beef gets done,
add your 1 can tomatoes, yellow corn, salt and pepper. When
your water
starts to boil again, add your egg noodles. Cook
until your noodles are done.
Cook your soup slow so the flavor goes through all of it.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Cook macaroni.
In a 2-quart dish, put a layer of macaroni and a layer of hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Slice cheese on top and add 1/2 of the can of tomato sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make dough of next 5 ingredients.
Pour over mixture.
Pour 1 quart peaches and half of juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top before baking.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Prepare rice and fry sausage; drain well.
Saute vegetables in oleo.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in large oblong casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup and celery soup

title: hot fudge pudding(old family favorite)
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar (white) together.
Add milk and mix. Spread in 2-quart baking dish (rectangular).
Spread brown sugar over batter.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Good plain, but great with vanilla ice cream. Cut into squares to serve, making sure you get the bottom sauce with each piece.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form into balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar (this is extra thin) and store in tight container.
Let balls harden slightly before serving.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar, beating well.
Add salt, vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon of nutmeg.
Gradually add scalded milk, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into pastry shell and sprinkle top with additional
nutmeg.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar, butter and chocolate until melted.
Add cream and flavoring.
Heat.

title: red cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Heat oil in skillet; add cabbage, apples and cloves.
Salt slightly.
Cook 25 minutes or until tender.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: grandma's pineapple salad
directions: Cream dry Jell-O with softened cream cheese.
Drain juice from fruit and add sufficient water to make 1 pint.
Heat juice to boiling point.
Gradually blend juice into cheese-Jell-O mixture. Stir until smooth.
When cool, pour over fruit and place in refrigerator to set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: joggin-in-a-jug
directions: Mix and chill.
Drink 2 ounces (1/4 cup) in the morning.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together with electric mixer until creamy.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of foil muffin baking cups.
Divide this mixture into 20 muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy pan.
Add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Pour chicken mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with pastry from recipe to follow.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, cream and slightly beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until a golden brown.

title: martha's cabbage roll casserole
directions: Cook meat, sausage, onion, salt and peppers until browned. Add chili powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, tomatoes, rice and half can of tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Chop head of cabbage and cook in separate pan.
Layer cabbage and then meat and rice mixture, ending with meat mixture in casserole dish.
Pour remaining half can of tomato sauce on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onion.
Then you layer raw ground beef, sliced potatoes, slices of onion, the mushroom soup, not condensed, salt and pepper.
Layer until all of the ingredients are used.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or potatoes are fork-tender.

title: sunday morning sausage
directions: Lightly butter a 9-inch ring mold (Bundt pan will do).
Mix ingredients well and pack into mold. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Take from oven and pour off excess fat.
Bake 25 minutes more. Turn onto heated plate and fill with scrambled eggs.

title: curried basmati rice
directions: Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray and heat.
Saute mushrooms, onions and peppers for about 5 minutes or until tender. Add rice, curry, salt and chicken broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer; cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes until rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: mock sour cream(low-fat, lo-cal)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container of an electric blender; process at medium-high speed until smooth and creamy.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve as a topping for baked potatoes.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups (about 9 calories per tablespoon).

title: cinnamon carrot muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Mix cereal and milk in another bowl; let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in carrots, raisins, sugar, oil and egg. Add to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon batter into muffin pan which has been sprayed with no stick cooking spray, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: freezer jam
directions: Bring to a boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Pour in containers.

title: corn
directions: Mix all together and bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jo's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars and flour. Beat in thoroughly the eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Stir in nuts. Pour into pie crusts. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: reese's pie
directions: Mix pudding according to directions using skim milk.
Mix in peanut butter while still warm.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours. Cut pie into 4 pieces.
Each piece is:
1 bread; 2 1/4 fat; 1 milk; 1 1/2 protein; no optional calories.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows, if you like.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Set rack in lower third of oven and preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Core and slice apples.
In a skillet, melt butter with brown sugar and one tablespoon water. Add apples and cook, stirring for 2 to 3 minutes.
Transfer cooked apples to the baking dish; allow to cool.
Cut cream cheese into cubes and arrange evenly over apples.
Cut slices of bread in half diagonally and layer over the apples to cover the whole dish.
In a large bowl, beat together eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour the egg mixture over the bread, taking care to dampen all the bread. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 40-50 minutes, until golden and puffed.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in pineapple, stir in bread cubes.
Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 1 hour uncovered, serve hot.
Serve with pork chops, ham or turkey.
